00:26.290 --> 00:31.760
December

00:27.570 --> 00:30.860
Adults often said that I sleep on the go.

00:35.910 --> 00:39.750
Hey! Where are you going?

00:41.370 --> 00:44.820
Please take me and my package to the city.

00:45.130 --> 00:48.420
Usually it is carried by my brother, but he has a cold.

00:48.710 --> 00:52.950
I'm here instead of... him...

00:53.370 --> 00:54.940
That's it...

00:54.940 --> 00:59.530
Don't sit like that, there's scattered gravel everywhere.

00:59.880 --> 01:04.620
First I'll take the nori, then I'll buy stuff for my brother and sister and go home.

01:06.230 --> 01:07.420
Yeah...

01:19.240 --> 01:20.540
Look.

01:21.290 --> 01:22.970
Here we are.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.220
Oh! Don't sleep on the go.

01:43.370 --> 01:47.670
Chocolate "Morinaga"

01:47.670 --> 01:49.710
New Year's sale in Hiroshima

01:54.570 --> 01:56.240
Chocolate - 10 yen.

01:56.280 --> 01:59.260
A large packet of caramel - 10 yen, small - 5 yen.

01:59.420 --> 02:00.880
Yo-yo - 10 yen.

02:00.730 --> 02:02.310
So, pull, pull.

02:05.820 --> 02:07.170
Look at this.

02:07.280 --> 02:09.000
Come in, please.

02:10.310 --> 02:12.240
Thank you very much.

02:17.760 --> 02:25.620
♪ So he squeezes in the chest from the radiance of the sky.

02:26.620 --> 02:38.730
♪ Today I look up again and I cannot hold back tears.

02:46.570 --> 02:55.310
♪ White clouds all float and swim.

02:56.400 --> 03:07.220
♪ Today all my dreams are confused and get lost.

03:07.770 --> 03:13.040
♪ Sadness, longing.

03:13.800 --> 03:18.970
♪ It's already intolerable.

03:19.130 --> 03:24.950
♪ Is there any salvation?

03:25.440 --> 03:33.170
♪ From this infinite emptiness?

03:30.750 --> 03:46.620
In This
Corner of
the World

03:50.200 --> 03:52.590
I lost my way in the city.

03:53.480 --> 03:55.510
Then I saw an uncle with a basket.

03:57.750 --> 04:01.330
Suzu, who is this?

04:01.550 --> 04:02.370
The monster.

04:02.550 --> 04:03.150
Eh?

04:03.600 --> 04:08.910
He said to me: "Climb up and look into your telescope".

04:11.110 --> 04:13.910
How well you can see!

04:16.350 --> 04:19.800
I fell inward, and there was an unfamiliar boy.

04:20.200 --> 04:23.910
He steals children, and he also stole me.

04:25.660 --> 04:27.240
That's bad.

04:27.730 --> 04:31.600
I need to return by evening to feed the chickens.

04:31.840 --> 04:35.350
I also need to see my father at the station.

04:35.350 --> 04:37.060
Me too, me too...

04:37.370 --> 04:41.260
If I don't get there before sunset, trouble will happen to me.

04:41.370 --> 04:43.460
What's the trouble with him?

04:43.460 --> 04:45.080
Now, see for yourself.

04:51.150 --> 04:52.350
Uncle, uncle.

04:51.640 --> 04:52.860
Aw, what?

04:53.660 --> 04:56.570
There's something strange, just look.

04:57.440 --> 04:58.860
And where is that?

05:04.220 --> 05:07.420
At night, the monsters sleep soundly.

05:08.710 --> 05:11.240
We're leaving him without dinner, poor fellow.

05:13.060 --> 05:15.240
Thanks, Urano Suzu.

05:15.400 --> 05:17.860
Oh, how do you know my name?

05:20.170 --> 05:21.910
Thanks, Urano Suzu.

05:22.890 --> 05:24.990
Hey, stop making noise!

05:26.130 --> 05:28.000
Maybe I was sleeping on the go.

05:28.440 --> 05:33.310
But everything that happened that day was like a dream.

05:35.640 --> 05:42.650
August

05:39.370 --> 05:41.820
Usually the sea looks like this.

05:43.280 --> 05:45.570
And at low tide it becomes like that.

05:47.680 --> 05:51.420
For the first time, we're going to the sea without adults. That's great!

05:51.860 --> 05:56.170
I'll say "Good morning, uncle, aunt and grandmother from Kusatsu."

05:56.710 --> 05:59.930
And mom and dad will be back in town.

06:00.110 --> 06:01.320
"Here's your watermelon."

06:01.580 --> 06:04.780
Ah! Give it to me, I want to carry it!

06:04.910 --> 06:05.530
Quiet!

06:07.220 --> 06:09.170
Here, it's your turn to carry it.

06:09.480 --> 06:12.150
My brother is always strict.

06:12.510 --> 06:13.530
Wait...

06:15.480 --> 06:17.000
Good morning.

06:18.040 --> 06:19.840
Dad and Mom...

06:23.750 --> 06:25.350
Here... the watermelon...

06:25.350 --> 06:27.910
Thanks, I'll take it away.

06:29.310 --> 06:31.060
Our little beauty.

06:31.420 --> 06:36.460
Every year my grandmother sews a new kimono for me.

06:35.280 --> 06:36.170
Here we are.

06:36.950 --> 06:41.240
Mom and Dad returned from the city with shopping and we went to the cemetery.

06:37.710 --> 06:40.910
The weather is good.

06:43.370 --> 06:44.840
What's going on now in Eba?

06:45.950 --> 06:49.350
Well, times are not all that simple.

06:49.350 --> 06:50.530
And that's right...

06:57.060 --> 06:58.510
Lot of things happened.

07:01.080 --> 07:03.660
But we children seemed to be fearless at the time.

07:04.330 --> 07:06.760
Even when seeing something unusual.

07:25.460 --> 07:28.020
Good afternoon.

07:33.620 --> 07:38.840
Say... do you want me to get more watermelon?

07:42.680 --> 07:44.060
Mom.

07:46.820 --> 07:49.710
Hey, the tide's going to be over soon.

07:50.660 --> 07:51.950
Come on, wake up.

07:53.150 --> 07:55.040
And you too, Sumi.

07:56.600 --> 07:57.240
Come on.

07:59.170 --> 08:02.550
Put it in the corner, she'll eat it.

08:03.280 --> 08:08.770
Uh-huh, tell me... if you leave her a kimono, will she dress?

08:09.800 --> 08:13.440
Suzu, you're a kind girl.

08:13.750 --> 08:18.620
They mentioned in school that it was a Zashiki-warashi house spirit.

08:19.040 --> 08:21.370
My brother explained everything to me.

08:21.370 --> 08:24.880
It seemed that both people and nature became a little kinder.

08:27.130 --> 08:29.600
You left a new kimono in Kusatsu?

08:29.600 --> 08:32.730
Go take it back. Idiot!

08:33.340 --> 08:35.480
My brother is the devil himself.

08:34.440 --> 08:37.350
I forgot how terrible my brother was.

08:39.330 --> 08:44.000
February

08:43.460 --> 08:45.420
Suzu, lower it further!

08:45.910 --> 08:47.330
It's not going to blow in the wind.

08:47.640 --> 08:48.220
Uh-huh.

08:49.770 --> 08:51.710
Mom, give me a couple yen.

08:51.970 --> 08:53.510
My pencil's out.

08:53.640 --> 08:55.310
You always buy one when you have money.

08:56.570 --> 08:59.020
And you draw nothing but horrible stuff.

09:01.970 --> 09:04.600
Sumi, want to exchange pencils?

09:04.600 --> 09:05.240
Nope.

09:05.240 --> 09:08.950
Suzu, is Mizuhara Tetsu at school every day?

09:09.240 --> 09:10.840
Eh? I think so...

09:16.530 --> 09:18.280
It's cold!

09:39.750 --> 09:41.020
It's so short.

09:41.660 --> 09:43.750
Is it enough for a whole week?

09:44.060 --> 09:46.260
Look, you shouldn't drop it there.

09:49.820 --> 09:51.930
A drawing lesson on a free topic.

09:52.240 --> 09:54.770
Those who are done can go home.

09:54.880 --> 09:55.880
Yes!

09:55.880 --> 09:57.640
Let's draw over here.

09:59.480 --> 10:01.240
Hmm, not bad.

10:01.550 --> 10:03.080
Good work, Urano.

10:03.550 --> 10:05.620
Suzu is such an artist.

10:08.440 --> 10:10.170
I came back!

10:12.460 --> 10:14.660
I'll go and collect some dry needles.

10:14.950 --> 10:16.040
Be safe.

10:34.880 --> 10:40.310
Mizuhara, you won't go home until you finish your picture?

10:40.800 --> 10:41.600
Go home?

10:42.550 --> 10:46.080
My parents drink all day, they don't even collect nori.

10:46.710 --> 10:49.680
I don't want to draw the sea... I hate it.

10:50.220 --> 10:51.660
Urano, reach out your hand.

10:56.620 --> 10:57.370
This is for you.

10:59.800 --> 11:00.950
Can I take it?

11:01.310 --> 11:04.060
Take it, it's my brother's pencil.

11:04.660 --> 11:06.350
The rabbits are jumping.

11:06.930 --> 11:10.280
When they rolled over, everything was the same.

11:11.130 --> 11:14.820
Draw me something, even though this is a stupid sea.

11:17.820 --> 11:21.150
Mizuhara, what kind of rabbits are these?

11:21.350 --> 11:22.020
What?

11:22.600 --> 11:26.880
Ah... the foam on the waves is similar to white rabbits.

11:27.660 --> 11:30.460
Mizuhara, take my brother.

11:30.640 --> 11:31.310
Don't want him.

11:32.260 --> 11:36.680
We have a rule: we see your brother, we run without looking back.

11:38.970 --> 11:45.710
Although, still... he, at least, isn't such a fool to go study to become a sailor and immediately drown.

11:46.880 --> 11:50.600
You know, they really look like rabbits.

11:53.080 --> 11:54.110
Done.

11:54.330 --> 11:55.640
I got your needles.

11:55.770 --> 11:56.930
Thank you.

11:58.750 --> 12:00.570
Something good happened.

12:01.350 --> 12:04.000
Of course, now you can go home.

12:04.910 --> 12:08.480
But such a sea... it's hard to even hate it.

12:13.830 --> 12:17.380
March

12:15.330 --> 12:19.760
The Imperial Navy is fighting bravely in the eastern waters of the Pacific...

12:16.710 --> 12:20.260
December

12:19.460 --> 12:23.750
Banzai! Banzai! Banzai!

12:19.760 --> 12:25.260
April

12:20.090 --> 12:23.320
Urano Suzu

12:20.090 --> 12:23.320
Bloody brother is in the army

12:25.300 --> 12:29.810
December

12:25.480 --> 12:28.950
Look at that, Morita's niece is already gathering.

12:29.170 --> 12:30.020
Exactly.

12:32.840 --> 12:34.970
What a wonderful outfit you have.

12:51.950 --> 12:56.260
You're doing good. Come, I made dinner.

12:57.220 --> 12:58.260
I'm coming!

13:01.510 --> 13:04.240
Suzu will find her husband far from here.

13:04.640 --> 13:05.680
Right?

13:06.000 --> 13:07.680
And for Sumi, someone close.

13:07.910 --> 13:13.350
Like a girl holding sticks, your new house will be so close.

13:15.240 --> 13:17.060
Granny, are you from afar?

13:18.200 --> 13:20.930
I was born in Furue.

13:21.130 --> 13:24.110
So it's nothing from Furue to Kusatsu.

13:24.240 --> 13:27.770
Think of the people that are getting married in Manchuria or some other places.

13:27.860 --> 13:31.730
Even after saying this, Urano Sumi later moved far from home.

13:32.000 --> 13:34.730
It's not interesting to live very closely.

13:39.020 --> 13:40.910
Suzu, hurry up back home.

13:40.970 --> 13:42.480
We got a phone call.

13:42.480 --> 13:48.550
They said that a man came to your house who wants to marry you. Straight from Kure.

13:48.660 --> 13:49.400
From Kure?

13:49.730 --> 13:53.130
Suzu, how old are you?

13:53.130 --> 13:57.240
Nineteen... no, eighteen.

13:57.750 --> 14:01.750
You can refuse if you don't like it, but go see him first.

14:01.750 --> 14:04.220
Suzu, come with me.

14:05.800 --> 14:11.240
I kept waiting for that day to come.
I made something for you.

14:11.750 --> 14:14.860
In it, you'll look like a princess.

14:17.000 --> 14:18.060
Thank you.

14:19.330 --> 14:23.620
The wedding ceremony will be at the groom's house.

14:24.570 --> 14:25.170
Yes...

14:25.170 --> 14:30.020
And in the evening he will ask you: "Have you taken an umbrella with you?".

14:31.280 --> 14:35.840
You will answer: "Yes, I took one, completely new."

14:36.510 --> 14:39.970
He will say: "Can I take it?".

14:39.970 --> 14:42.330
And you tell him: "Take it."

14:42.860 --> 14:43.950
What for?

14:44.350 --> 14:45.310
For everything.

14:45.570 --> 14:47.840
So, I become an adult.

14:48.750 --> 14:55.110
Once in Kure... there's a big military port there... and there's a lot of sailors...

15:00.930 --> 15:01.910
Mizuhara?

15:04.150 --> 15:05.330
Long-time no see...

15:05.600 --> 15:07.040
Get home already.

15:07.110 --> 15:07.640
Eh?

15:08.000 --> 15:12.800
Your mother made such a mess, all the neighbors know.

15:14.240 --> 15:18.950
Oh, I was so scared. I really thought they were giving me away to you.

15:18.950 --> 15:20.150
Are you a fool?

15:20.620 --> 15:24.460
I went to my brother's funeral.
He drowned seven years ago.

15:26.930 --> 15:29.600
So you don't know who he is?

15:30.170 --> 15:31.080
Not at all.

15:31.770 --> 15:34.280
Maybe I got confused with Sumi.

15:35.150 --> 15:37.600
She will be more beautiful.

15:38.350 --> 15:40.680
Or maybe not.

15:41.400 --> 15:46.770
It seems that he met her somewhere when he was studying at a local school.

15:48.020 --> 15:50.930
But it wasn't easy to find you.

15:51.220 --> 15:56.840
Three years ago I decided to stop collecting nori and went to work at the factory.

15:58.040 --> 16:00.480
She will come back soon.

16:01.420 --> 16:04.350
I don't know if it's good or bad.

16:03.400 --> 16:04.260
Help yourself.

16:04.570 --> 16:08.240
I had some kind of caramel taste in my mouth.

16:08.370 --> 16:09.800
I don't know why.

16:10.200 --> 16:11.510
It's really cold.

16:12.330 --> 16:13.930
It's a mess.

16:15.020 --> 16:17.420
I can refuse if I want to.

16:18.020 --> 16:20.880
But how can I decide if I don't know him at all...

16:20.880 --> 16:22.060
Sorry to intrude.

16:23.170 --> 16:23.820
Yes?

16:25.930 --> 16:28.080
We got lost in the city.

16:28.080 --> 16:30.020
Where is the train stop?

16:30.510 --> 16:31.420
Over there.

16:31.420 --> 16:32.550
Forgive us.

16:32.730 --> 16:36.080
A young sailor already showed us the way.

16:36.530 --> 16:40.510
Ah, it's a little weird here.

16:40.680 --> 16:45.240
They got lost in the mountains, but a little strange woman helped them out.

16:48.360 --> 16:52.610
February

16:49.750 --> 16:53.110
Why am I so confused?

16:51.070 --> 16:53.570
Hiroshima

16:54.360 --> 16:56.990
Hiroshima

16:54.550 --> 16:57.600
When did I become so?

16:56.450 --> 16:59.410
Kaitaichi

16:58.950 --> 17:01.620
Yano

17:01.120 --> 17:03.870
Saka

17:03.000 --> 17:05.210
Coyaura

17:07.710 --> 17:08.839
It was a long trip.

17:09.000 --> 17:13.819
The train will enter the tunnel, close all the windows.

17:23.280 --> 17:24.800
It's hard to breathe.

17:29.310 --> 17:33.040
Kure! Kure!

17:34.660 --> 17:37.220
This is the training fleet.

17:51.570 --> 17:54.280
Excuse me. Excuse me.

17:56.660 --> 17:59.530
Is the bus broken again?

17:59.910 --> 18:01.570
Oh, Mrs. Kobayashi.

18:00.970 --> 18:04.000
Welcome, Mrs. Kobayashi.

18:04.200 --> 18:06.350
The weather is good today.

18:06.480 --> 18:08.930
All that matters is that everyone is healthy.

18:10.060 --> 18:12.080
From now on, I'll be grateful to you.

18:12.570 --> 18:15.080
I beg your indulgence for my foolishness.

18:15.080 --> 18:20.020
I'm Kobayashi, the groom's aunt.
I'll be a matchmaker at the ceremony.

18:20.130 --> 18:23.480
She did not even remember the name of the groom.

18:23.480 --> 18:25.440
This unreasonableness frightens me.

18:32.420 --> 18:36.550
Oh, how high they we climb.

18:36.750 --> 18:39.000
It seems their house is above all others.

18:39.220 --> 18:40.370
This way, please.

18:40.760 --> 18:43.260
HOUJO

18:41.170 --> 18:43.020
They're here!

18:43.400 --> 18:46.460
Forgive me that the ceremony is so modest and not crowded.

18:46.800 --> 18:50.280
It's ok, my daughter is very shy, it's even better.

18:48.060 --> 18:49.170
Suzu.

18:49.880 --> 18:53.350
In fact, I wonder why I dressed in this kimono.

18:55.750 --> 18:58.530
Why are you undressing, Suzu?

19:06.020 --> 19:08.020
This is a feast.

19:08.020 --> 19:11.000
It's a pity that our elder son could not come.

19:11.000 --> 19:13.420
Now it's hard to get together.

19:13.420 --> 19:17.640
Thank you for bringing so many nori and vegetables with you.

19:13.800 --> 19:18.860
Eat more. We must all eat without fail until the evening.

19:19.000 --> 19:21.710
And the roast is also very tasty.

19:22.770 --> 19:26.020
Lucky for you, he's such a quiet guy.

19:26.200 --> 19:28.600
I think there's not a single troublemaker in the whole house.

19:28.440 --> 19:30.420
Unless you become one.

19:28.860 --> 19:31.110
Don't forget us, come visit.

19:31.600 --> 19:34.330
Be happy with your stay!!

19:34.460 --> 19:36.400
Bye!

19:38.330 --> 19:39.600
I'll be back.

19:44.440 --> 19:48.080
Err.. who is she?

19:48.280 --> 19:53.570
Well, she's someone that will help with the household chores so you can rest more.

19:53.570 --> 19:54.280
Yes.

19:56.130 --> 19:58.000
Mother, father.

19:58.280 --> 20:00.370
From now on, I will be gracious to you.

20:00.460 --> 20:02.750
We're happy, too.

20:03.020 --> 20:08.240
My legs hurt, thanks for the help, Suzu.

20:08.860 --> 20:09.350
Of course.

20:10.730 --> 20:14.750
I'm sorry. When Keiko cooks, she burns everything.

20:15.000 --> 20:19.420
Yeah, she's his married older sister.

20:37.880 --> 20:39.660
It's lighting from the training ships.

20:41.840 --> 20:44.510
Where is mom and dad now?

20:51.530 --> 20:54.730
Thanks for the futon.

20:55.220 --> 20:55.930
Uh-huh.

21:00.750 --> 21:01.800
Oh, Suzu...

21:02.370 --> 21:02.970
What?

21:04.150 --> 21:06.350
Did you took an umbrella?

21:10.680 --> 21:14.530
Yes. I absolutely did... a new one...

21:15.530 --> 21:17.130
Can I take it?

21:24.530 --> 21:25.240
Here you go.

21:27.640 --> 21:29.080
Hungry?

21:33.110 --> 21:35.130
Well, it's not ripe yet.

21:36.750 --> 21:39.420
You have not eaten anything for a day.

21:40.220 --> 21:43.240
You do eat with your mouth, like everyone else. It's calming.

21:45.110 --> 21:46.710
Don't be afraid, don't be afraid.

21:46.710 --> 21:50.040
I drink like everyone else. Also with my mouth.

21:52.200 --> 21:55.860
Listen, have we seen each other before?

21:57.620 --> 22:00.420
Have we seen? You don't remember?

22:00.600 --> 22:04.570
Sorry, I'm a little distracted.

22:04.570 --> 22:06.420
It was a long time ago.

22:08.640 --> 22:11.480
But I remember this birthmark well.

22:44.770 --> 22:49.260
We collect water from a common well nearby.

23:10.450 --> 23:28.300
New Guinea, division No. 5173

23:10.450 --> 23:28.300
to Mr. Urano Yoichi

