24:03.100 --> 24:07.090
The transmitted board

24:03.100 --> 24:07.090
Upper Naganoka's neighbors association

24:03.240 --> 24:04.860
The distribution?

24:04.970 --> 24:09.200
With this couple, it won't be easy.

24:05.050 --> 24:09.090
♪ You open the window !!!!
and you see a familiar face.

24:09.630 --> 24:13.220
♪ You are handed over a transfer board.

24:09.770 --> 24:11.170
Nice to meet you.

24:11.370 --> 24:12.330
I'm Tita.

24:12.330 --> 24:13.330
And I'm Karia.

24:13.390 --> 24:18.300
♪ You learn something, write something.

24:18.660 --> 24:19.620
This again?

24:19.840 --> 24:21.710
What's wrong again?

24:22.080 --> 24:24.120
You just measure it by eye.

24:24.120 --> 24:24.960
Coming.

24:24.960 --> 24:26.140
It's not fair.

24:26.170 --> 24:27.110
It's fair.

24:27.110 --> 24:30.820
♪ Top, top, top, this is the neighbors go.

24:27.370 --> 24:28.370
How can it be?

24:28.570 --> 24:29.570
What else?

24:29.800 --> 24:32.510
Well, why do you do this?

24:31.320 --> 24:35.320
♪ Again, there are some problems with the products.

24:32.680 --> 24:33.750
How should I?

24:34.820 --> 24:35.840
Hold it, hold it.

24:35.740 --> 24:39.410
♪ Will teach you through the fence

24:35.840 --> 24:37.330
You're splashing like this.

24:39.700 --> 24:43.960
♪ how to cook the porridge correctly.

24:42.730 --> 24:44.660
Oy-yoy-yoy-yoy-yoy.

24:44.660 --> 24:45.750
I'm sorry.

24:46.150 --> 24:48.970
Don't underestimate the danger of incendiary bombs.

24:49.620 --> 24:51.860
In case of one hitting your house,

24:51.970 --> 24:55.620
it is necessary to take measures to neutralize it.

24:55.930 --> 25:02.380
Depending on the type of bomb, the measures can be different.

24:56.550 --> 25:01.220
Sit closer... well, it's cold today.

25:02.380 --> 25:05.440
The main thing at that moment is not to panic.

25:04.680 --> 25:07.220
This has become my everyday life.

25:08.360 --> 25:13.700
March

25:18.770 --> 25:22.220
Ah, this is Keiko's old dress.

25:22.420 --> 25:24.350
Now it's gathering dust.

25:24.710 --> 25:28.860
Once she was walking in it with her fiancé.

25:29.440 --> 25:34.040
In the cinema, at the fairs and in the expensive restaurants.

25:36.570 --> 25:39.480
Sister can be really fashionable.

25:40.240 --> 25:42.680
It was a completely different time back then.

25:43.950 --> 25:49.880
Shūsaku was in the fourth grade when they ceased to build warships after the peace conference.

25:50.860 --> 25:56.880
My husband, like many others, lost his job.

25:57.370 --> 26:03.750
And Keiko stated that her husband and herself would find their own work.

26:03.910 --> 26:08.370
Okay, I'll try not to give it up.

26:10.000 --> 26:13.570
It seemed back then that things couldn't go worse.

26:14.730 --> 26:17.750
I really miss that time.

26:27.600 --> 26:28.840
Good afternoon.

26:29.600 --> 26:30.570
I'm home.

26:31.770 --> 26:33.840
Welcome back, sister.

26:36.750 --> 26:37.510
Shame.

26:40.260 --> 26:43.600
Why is this? It seems quite fit rice to me.

26:44.010 --> 26:45.500
I'm talking about you!

26:46.160 --> 26:47.570
You're from Hiroshima, are you not?

26:47.570 --> 26:49.690
I thought you had some taste.

26:49.980 --> 26:52.730
So what are these patched pants?

26:53.260 --> 26:54.950
Are you grilling beans?

26:53.280 --> 27:01.060
Girls should dress decently. Are not you ashamed of yourself?

26:55.170 --> 26:57.910
Oh, welcome back, Harumi.

26:57.910 --> 27:02.750
Although I obeyed, Mom was angry all day for some reason.

27:02.750 --> 27:06.330
I'm sorry, but I have nothing else.

27:03.200 --> 27:04.330
True?

27:06.330 --> 27:07.550
So take it!

27:11.930 --> 27:16.040
And the rice in that sack is not a gift. It's my and Harumi's share.

27:18.130 --> 27:19.620
What's with you, Keiko?

27:19.860 --> 27:21.440
Please understand, mother...

27:21.460 --> 27:24.510
Yes, well, I tried.

27:26.400 --> 27:26.930
Ouch!

27:27.420 --> 27:29.840
Well, again. No, not like that.

27:30.020 --> 27:33.440
No one's will ever get married to you like that.

27:33.680 --> 27:35.440
Well, it's not really necessary.

27:42.570 --> 27:45.910
She's got a belt...

27:47.260 --> 27:48.420
Yeah, I see.

28:04.020 --> 28:07.880
Cut, unfold, cut again.

28:08.460 --> 28:10.800
Fold and sew.

28:11.930 --> 28:15.510
Sew a rubber band and it's ready for business. Let's do it.

28:19.280 --> 28:20.880
I'm Kuromaru Harumi.

28:20.880 --> 28:23.110
Hojo Suzu, good afternoon.

28:24.220 --> 28:26.000
Suzu, lend me some thread.

28:27.040 --> 28:28.600
Is this okay?

28:44.440 --> 28:45.240
Wow.

28:46.170 --> 28:48.130
Suzu, are you leaving?

28:48.170 --> 28:49.730
Yes, for the distribution.

28:50.370 --> 28:53.930
I will go myself, give me the purse and the card.

28:54.460 --> 28:56.600
Okay, be safe.

29:11.080 --> 29:12.420
Welcome back.

29:17.680 --> 29:19.640
Enough, let me do it.

29:20.970 --> 29:21.640
Eh?

29:28.970 --> 29:31.110
Listen, Mom!

29:33.510 --> 29:35.950
Yes, yes, what do you want...

29:35.950 --> 29:37.880
Where are all the pots?

29:56.130 --> 29:59.150
Oh, Keiko and Harumi came back.

29:59.370 --> 30:00.110
Together?

30:00.530 --> 30:01.930
Welcome back, Dad.

30:02.000 --> 30:03.730
Well, have a good rest.

30:05.770 --> 30:10.420
Wow... My sister cooked, but nothing burned out.

30:10.600 --> 30:12.710
Listen, Shūsaku!

30:12.730 --> 30:18.460
You know, sister told me how to sew a new kimono.

30:20.440 --> 30:21.340
It's nothing.

30:21.740 --> 30:24.150
My mother has aching legs.

30:24.480 --> 30:28.220
A girl like you probably doesn't know how to help.

30:28.860 --> 30:32.130
I'll stay here for a while.

30:33.310 --> 30:36.950
Suzu, don't you want to go to Hiroshima?

30:38.330 --> 30:38.750
Eh?

30:39.620 --> 30:40.880
That's okay.

30:46.030 --> 30:48.010
The castle of Hiroshima. Urano Suzu.

30:46.310 --> 30:47.730
I'm home.

30:48.080 --> 30:49.730
Oh, I'm tired.

30:49.910 --> 30:51.040
Welcome back.

30:51.910 --> 30:53.620
It's eight already.

30:53.880 --> 30:55.620
There was a lot of work.

30:57.060 --> 30:58.840
Is that belt a "sennninbari"?
(千人針 thousand-person-stitches belt)

30:58.840 --> 31:01.510
Yes. Sumi, will you also make a stitch?

31:01.550 --> 31:02.370
Yes.

31:03.130 --> 31:05.420
Hey, Suzu, it's time to wake up!

31:05.800 --> 31:06.970
Y..yes!

31:09.370 --> 31:10.860
Here, sit down and have supper.

31:11.930 --> 31:17.150
Oh, I dreamed that I got married and left for Kure.

31:18.770 --> 31:20.510
Are you awake now?

31:19.660 --> 31:20.370
Yes.

31:20.860 --> 31:25.000
Well, my husband's sister said, "go to Hiroshima."

31:26.060 --> 31:28.110
I don't quite understand why.

31:28.510 --> 31:30.510
Ah! To visit?

31:30.710 --> 31:35.800
And, mom and dad, you said to me, "we're so sorry that we haven't noticed so far."

31:36.880 --> 31:41.550
"Go, stay two or three days with your relatives," his sister said.

31:41.820 --> 31:45.910
If you want to go, we don't mind.

31:46.970 --> 31:49.550
Did you write to Yoichi in the army?

31:49.640 --> 31:51.110
Yeah, I wrote.

31:51.420 --> 31:55.840
But no answer... it didn't come.

31:58.660 --> 32:00.060
They are far away.

32:00.060 --> 32:02.080
And they probably are not up to it.

32:02.550 --> 32:05.750
Most likely the address was confused.

32:06.710 --> 32:08.750
Bath! Bath!

32:08.880 --> 32:11.020
Sumi, is it hard to be a volunteer?

32:11.020 --> 32:12.600
I got used to it already.

32:12.600 --> 32:14.880
All the engines stinks of oil.

32:15.260 --> 32:18.130
Dangerous work is terrible.

32:18.370 --> 32:23.040
It's not as cold as the nori harvesting, and there are good sides.

32:23.220 --> 32:27.880
A nice lieutenant sometimes secretly
gives me coupons for lunch.

32:27.880 --> 32:29.000
Oh, Wicked.

32:29.150 --> 32:31.930
Be careful not to hear any military secrets inadvertently.

32:32.260 --> 32:35.660
Suzu, how are you coping?
Is Kure a good place?

32:37.480 --> 32:39.840
I'm still just sorting it out.

32:41.640 --> 32:48.330
I think I just found out a very important military secret.

32:48.330 --> 32:49.420
What are you talking about?

32:49.420 --> 32:50.310
Good night.

32:52.550 --> 32:53.620
Suzu.

32:53.620 --> 32:54.440
What?

32:55.330 --> 32:57.840
You have a bald spot.

32:57.840 --> 32:58.420
What!?

33:00.200 --> 33:03.280
Bye Suzu, I'm going to work!

33:04.020 --> 33:06.040
Victory requires special measures.

33:06.040 --> 33:09.570
Starting next month, even short trips will be limited.

33:10.260 --> 33:11.260
Take care of yourself.

33:12.640 --> 33:15.600
Well, I have a job in the women's association.

33:15.680 --> 33:18.570
What? You work too?

33:33.370 --> 33:36.420
Dad gave me some money.

34:08.480 --> 34:09.420
Farewell.

34:11.330 --> 34:12.969
Farewell, Hiroshima.

34:17.719 --> 34:19.719
To date, all tickets  SOLD

34:17.719 --> 34:19.719
Hiroshima Station

34:19.280 --> 34:21.400
And you came back here?

34:22.000 --> 34:24.860
I already sympathize with your new family.

34:33.480 --> 34:34.350
I'm back.

34:35.210 --> 34:41.300
April

34:36.460 --> 34:38.860
His sister still lives with us.

34:42.679 --> 34:45.929
Mom, give me an inkwell.

34:46.260 --> 34:47.750
I'm not going to, Harumi.

34:48.550 --> 34:50.260
Give me.

34:50.550 --> 34:54.150
Suzu, what did you say to Harumi?

34:55.909 --> 34:59.040
Can I pass the board on?

34:59.240 --> 35:00.280
Take it.

35:01.730 --> 35:02.950
I'm going.

35:03.280 --> 35:06.840
She has been like that since she came back from Hiroshima.

35:07.310 --> 35:09.370
It's nothing, she's just being childish.

35:09.370 --> 35:11.840
Thank you for your concern.

35:12.640 --> 35:13.730
Well give me.

35:13.730 --> 35:15.280
I clearly said no.

35:15.510 --> 35:16.950
Please.

35:17.310 --> 35:19.750
You don't need it!

35:44.150 --> 35:45.440
Welcome back.

35:47.150 --> 35:49.020
Field grass?

35:49.260 --> 35:52.750
Yes. It can be added to the food.

35:54.840 --> 35:57.350
Here, all the dandelions are white.

35:58.020 --> 35:59.660
And they are not in Eba?

36:00.440 --> 36:02.750
Oh, that one is still yellow.

36:05.530 --> 36:07.550
It must have been brought from afar.

36:09.840 --> 36:14.480
I wondered why you were so down.
Did you fall in love in Hiroshima?

36:14.750 --> 36:15.820
Not at all.

36:22.400 --> 36:24.060
Look! There!

36:24.330 --> 36:26.060
The aircraft carriers arrived today.

36:26.510 --> 36:28.530
Ship and carriers, I guess.

36:28.530 --> 36:29.710
The big ones.

36:31.150 --> 36:33.350
And these small ships are destroyers.

36:33.880 --> 36:35.880
There are also submarines from Germany.

36:36.160 --> 36:39.400
And similar to an ordinary ship, their mother ship.

36:44.420 --> 36:46.150
Oh, the dandelion's seed are flying.

36:46.480 --> 36:47.080
Where?

36:47.260 --> 36:49.000
Yes, over there.

36:49.730 --> 36:50.710
I can see for myself.

36:53.840 --> 36:56.220
Shūsaku, what is this?

36:56.680 --> 36:58.330
Is it a ship?

36:58.600 --> 36:59.770
It's the Yamato.

37:00.600 --> 37:04.330
The largest warship in the world, built in our local port.

37:05.950 --> 37:07.800
And there are people on it?

37:08.220 --> 37:09.060
Yes.

37:12.000 --> 37:13.970
There's a team of two thousand seven hundred.

37:17.110 --> 37:19.770
Two thousand seven hundred people?

37:20.350 --> 37:21.350
Exactly.

37:21.800 --> 37:24.220
Tell her "welcome home", Suzu.

37:26.680 --> 37:31.130
Does someone cook food for all these people every day?

37:31.020 --> 37:31.710
Suzu.

37:31.510 --> 37:32.710
And more laundry...

37:37.840 --> 37:39.130
I'm sorry.

37:39.480 --> 37:40.800
You didn't hurt yourself?

37:40.800 --> 37:43.570
No, I think I'm okay.

37:53.510 --> 37:57.950
You know, Suzu, if you're too nervous, you'll grow bald faster.

37:58.220 --> 37:59.840
You noticed.

38:00.240 --> 38:05.260
Please, let me paint Suzu's bald spot.

38:05.370 --> 38:09.260
If I give it to you, you'll be covered in ink from head to toe.

38:11.640 --> 38:15.310
And then his sister returned to her husband's house.

38:15.660 --> 38:18.060
It's time for me to cook dinner.

38:18.670 --> 38:22.670
Today
Everything's
sold out.

38:18.670 --> 38:22.670
Do the
queue
again.

38:18.670 --> 38:22.670
Confidence
in getting some
can't be bought
with money.

38:18.670 --> 38:22.670
We don't know
when new arrival
will happen.

38:18.820 --> 38:21.950
There are less and less products being distributed.

38:19.230 --> 38:23.980
May

38:23.240 --> 38:27.370
Only four sardines per family of four.

38:28.510 --> 38:29.460
Mom!

38:28.620 --> 38:31.040
But at least I can add something to the usual greens.

38:31.460 --> 38:34.530
It's necessary to do the queue to buy soybean pulp.

38:35.620 --> 38:36.710
Ah, I see.

38:38.400 --> 38:42.370
Violet, stellaria, horsetail.

38:42.910 --> 38:47.020
Dandelion, sourdough, dried sardines, soybean pulp.

38:47.200 --> 38:50.930
Potatoes, sweet potatoes, wheat flour, plum seeds.

38:53.660 --> 38:55.510
Cut the sweet potatoes.

38:55.800 --> 38:59.930
Macerate the leaves in boiling water.

39:00.240 --> 39:04.280
Mix them with wheat flour and put everything together.

39:04.460 --> 39:06.110
And dinner is ready.

39:06.110 --> 39:08.600
Without Keiko around, it's so quiet.

39:08.820 --> 39:11.060
What's not eaten, you can dry it.

39:12.680 --> 39:14.040
So, let's continue.

39:14.550 --> 39:18.060
Fill rice with five times the volume of water and cook the porridge.

39:18.800 --> 39:22.080
Add the pieces of potatoes and cook for another 10 minutes.

39:22.970 --> 39:25.020
Now we put the leaves of the stellaria.

39:25.620 --> 39:28.530
We cut the daikon and dandelion root.

39:28.530 --> 39:31.110
Fry them with sugar and soy sauce.

39:31.910 --> 39:36.640
We add dandelion leaves and soybean pulp. A little more frying.

39:38.510 --> 39:42.510
Cover with the remaining daikon, add some leaves and salt.

39:44.220 --> 39:47.800
Pour water in miso-nabe, add the plum seeds and boil it.

39:48.020 --> 39:52.440
Add the sardines to make a broth and don't put the lid.

39:52.710 --> 39:54.800
Add salt to taste.

39:54.860 --> 39:58.220
That's great. Did Karia teach you that?

39:58.220 --> 40:00.550
The ration of rice was reduced by half.

40:01.060 --> 40:02.800
We'll eat porridge from sweet potatoes.

40:02.800 --> 40:03.600
Okay.

40:03.820 --> 40:05.950
Tomorrow I will prepare something interesting again.

40:06.600 --> 40:12.880
The loyal Kusunoki, when resisting at the gate, came up with ways to make the rice reserve last longer.

40:14.460 --> 40:17.280
First fry the rice well.

40:18.220 --> 40:22.200
Add a three-fold portion of water and simmer on a small fire.

40:23.770 --> 40:27.110
To save rice and not to waste firewood for nothing,

40:27.770 --> 40:32.860
Trust his great Japanese invention: a fireless cooker.

40:33.840 --> 40:35.310
We wait till tomorrow.

40:38.110 --> 40:43.570
We warm up yesterday's fish broth, add violet and miso.

40:44.280 --> 40:47.400
In the morning we stoke the fire and finish the rice.

40:47.970 --> 40:49.000
It's ready!

40:49.640 --> 40:52.880
The famous Kusunoki Masashige rice!

40:53.840 --> 40:56.040
I filled Dad's bento with it.

40:58.640 --> 41:00.930
Wow, what a big portion today.

41:01.040 --> 41:02.530
The rice is all swollen.

41:02.770 --> 41:05.150
Is there really such a way of cooking?

41:05.150 --> 41:05.820
Yes.

41:06.000 --> 41:07.820
We're going to eat.

41:18.150 --> 41:19.170
We are going.

41:18.640 --> 41:19.660
Sorry to see you go.

41:19.750 --> 41:25.820
If Kusunoki ate this voluntarily, he really was a great hero.

41:26.420 --> 41:28.130
Probably...

41:28.340 --> 41:33.090
June

41:30.280 --> 41:34.080
Air alarm!

41:35.310 --> 41:38.480
Air alarm!

41:45.080 --> 41:47.080
There's nothing on the radio.

41:47.350 --> 41:49.710
Is Shūsaku still at work?

41:50.020 --> 41:50.600
Yes.

41:50.600 --> 41:56.080
But if you think from the enemy's way of view, it's logical to start bombing Kyūshū.

41:56.550 --> 41:59.440
There's no point hitting here in the mountains.

42:00.860 --> 42:02.280
They just turned off the lights.

42:05.480 --> 42:07.330
Be careful up there.

42:08.110 --> 42:10.200
They should remove those houses.

42:10.950 --> 42:13.750
The city needs a fire wall.

42:13.750 --> 42:14.550
Right.

42:14.770 --> 42:17.480
But we'll definitely not do it.

42:18.060 --> 42:19.460
Poor things.

42:19.910 --> 42:22.420
They will have to look for a new home.

42:23.710 --> 42:24.550
Thank you.

42:25.730 --> 42:27.080
It's my pleasure.

42:28.480 --> 42:30.370
There will be plenty of firewood.

42:31.040 --> 42:33.420
Because my house was wrecked.

42:33.600 --> 42:34.730
That's bad.

42:35.240 --> 42:37.910
He had to go to Simonoseki.

42:38.910 --> 42:40.910
This is not a good thing, I am directly divorced.

42:42.680 --> 42:46.060
Don't worry, I'll find a job and I will not be a freeloader.

42:46.970 --> 42:49.750
It should be taken into account that there is more people around now.

42:50.680 --> 42:51.730
Will that do?

42:51.730 --> 42:52.750
Yeah.

42:53.630 --> 42:58.380
July

42:57.710 --> 43:00.680
Yesterday they fired from the
very top of the Hagamine mountain.

43:00.930 --> 43:03.840
How did they bring the guns so high?

43:03.840 --> 43:05.750
Everything is becoming more and more dangerous.

43:06.350 --> 43:08.110
Thank you so much.

43:06.910 --> 43:08.000
And you, too.

43:08.880 --> 43:12.800
Well, the shelter became famous.

43:12.800 --> 43:13.510
Yes.

43:14.840 --> 43:18.220
It has been hard work, my legs can't hold me anymore.

43:19.330 --> 43:23.660
Keiko helped us out, bringing tatami boards from home.

43:26.000 --> 43:29.280
Shūsaku, why is she here?

43:29.950 --> 43:31.820
Simply, it happened.

43:33.130 --> 43:35.660
But now we need to clean up.

43:38.150 --> 43:43.000
Shūsaku, should I take this earth into the fields?

43:43.000 --> 43:46.550
Yes, of course, just be careful.

43:47.240 --> 43:49.770
Ah, you're here, too.

43:49.950 --> 43:52.130
Yeah, I'm watching the ships.

43:55.220 --> 43:57.440
Today a lot of them have gathered.

43:57.440 --> 44:01.620
The Yamato is the biggest.
The second one is the Musashi.

44:02.000 --> 44:06.000
There are many cruisers, but there are no aircraft carriers.

44:07.840 --> 44:11.130
This is the Tone, she has no towers behind her.

44:11.480 --> 44:13.130
Is she an aircraft carrier?

44:13.460 --> 44:17.730
Wow, that's great. How much you know.

44:17.910 --> 44:20.950
Yeah. I learned this from my brother.

44:21.570 --> 44:24.680
I see. I also know something.

44:25.730 --> 44:26.460
These are destroyers.

44:26.460 --> 44:26.950
Yeah.

44:27.440 --> 44:29.040
And there's something small floating around.

44:30.200 --> 44:31.710
It's a boat.

44:33.460 --> 44:35.370
Do you want me to tell you something?

44:36.220 --> 44:38.020
Do you see that huge cloud?

44:38.420 --> 44:38.970
Yeah.

44:38.970 --> 44:40.970
These are called "anvils".

44:41.150 --> 44:41.800
Yes.

44:42.370 --> 44:43.800
Oh, and it will rain very hard.

44:44.240 --> 44:44.820
Eh?

44:48.240 --> 44:49.260
Shūsaku!

44:48.930 --> 44:51.930
Let's hide in here for now.

45:01.220 --> 45:02.170
Thanks.

45:09.710 --> 45:11.280
I can do it myself.

45:12.640 --> 45:14.460
Are you very fond of ships?

45:14.570 --> 45:15.020
What?

45:15.370 --> 45:17.080
I spoke with Harumi.

45:17.310 --> 45:21.000
Ah... It was not I who taught Harumi.

45:21.620 --> 45:22.660
It was He-bo.

45:22.750 --> 45:23.370
Hee?

45:23.880 --> 45:27.150
Yes. He also likes ships.

45:27.710 --> 45:29.420
One day you will meet him.

45:30.220 --> 45:33.370
This Hisao, is this him?

45:34.150 --> 45:34.950
Yes.

45:45.950 --> 45:49.240
Now we kiss beside his name.

45:54.130 --> 45:56.880
Well, it was just a little sprinkle.

45:57.200 --> 45:59.080
You can go home already.

45:59.620 --> 46:00.660
Listen...

46:00.860 --> 46:05.200
This is fine when the family has a friendly relationship.

46:05.620 --> 46:09.820
Yes, husband and wife that loves each other. How lovely.

46:09.820 --> 46:11.330
Keiko?

46:14.240 --> 46:18.860
They really were close to each other, both so tall.

46:19.660 --> 46:24.910
Could it be that something happened to her husband?

46:25.130 --> 46:29.440
He was tall and thin, he was not even accepted into the army.

46:29.680 --> 46:31.400
He probably was too thin.

46:32.860 --> 46:39.170
When my father found a new job, my sister went to buy him a present.

46:39.570 --> 46:42.020
She met a young merchant.

46:39.570 --> 46:42.020
Kuromura Watch Shop

46:43.150 --> 46:47.730
They got married and ran a watch shop together.

46:48.730 --> 46:52.020
But you know what kind of character Keiko is.

46:52.510 --> 46:54.910
She quarreled with all of his family.

46:55.400 --> 47:01.150
Then her husband died and she had to manage the shop alone.

47:01.480 --> 47:06.310
Then there was some demolition and now, there is nothing left.

47:08.370 --> 47:11.280
Hisao is still the heir of the Kuromura family.

47:11.910 --> 47:14.400
He is now in Simonosaki.

47:14.400 --> 47:17.550
Naturally, it's hard for her.

47:18.260 --> 47:22.220
An happy family, where everyone smiles.

47:23.110 --> 47:24.660
Probably.

47:33.330 --> 47:35.150
I'll quickly go check the beds.

47:48.950 --> 47:53.480
Such simple things, but I didn't understand them for several months.

47:54.020 --> 47:56.040
How stupid I am.

48:00.860 --> 48:02.200
This is the Yamato.

48:03.680 --> 48:04.910
Like this.

48:11.020 --> 48:13.280
Well, I'm just...

48:11.760 --> 48:14.680
Military police Kempeitai.

48:15.150 --> 48:18.860
It's just a drawing for my niece.

48:18.860 --> 48:20.600
Do you know this woman?

48:20.600 --> 48:22.040
Ke... Kempei?

48:23.330 --> 48:27.710
To make sketches of the coastline is an act of espionage!

48:27.710 --> 48:33.460
Her face looks so innocent, but who knows what insidious plans ripen in her heart.

48:34.800 --> 48:40.220
This woman's husband serves as a clerk in the naval court.

48:40.460 --> 48:44.200
Maybe she's looking for a way to steal military secrets?

48:45.060 --> 48:47.170
Maybe she tried to send signals to someone?

48:47.680 --> 48:50.570
Maybe you found tables with codes in her things?

48:50.660 --> 48:53.970
Maybe you're hiding something? Confess!

48:55.970 --> 48:58.460
Consider that you got off lightly.

48:58.770 --> 49:03.310
Keep an eye on her, now no one can be trusted.

49:15.350 --> 49:16.460
I'm home.

49:17.550 --> 49:20.710
Why are all the clothes scattered around?

49:20.910 --> 49:24.910
Oh, Shūsaku, Suzu was almost arrested.

49:27.820 --> 49:30.220
Suzu, come here.

49:38.130 --> 49:41.060
Although in such a small book, you won't be able to draw much.

49:43.420 --> 49:49.280
You really like drawing so much, will you draw me sometime?

49:50.260 --> 49:54.400
It's probably better not to draw you.

49:56.730 --> 49:59.260
We have a spy in Suzu.

49:59.930 --> 50:02.910
Shūsaku, how can you hold back?

50:03.110 --> 50:06.660
We so apologized to them.

50:06.660 --> 50:08.680
And they bursted out laughing.

50:08.680 --> 50:11.350
When you try not to laugh, your face gets even weirder.

50:14.660 --> 50:19.480
It was like she didn't notice anything around her.

50:19.710 --> 50:23.950
For some people, a naive person seems so cunning.

50:24.310 --> 50:28.600
The only thing Suzu remembers about my job is that it ends at six in the evening.

50:28.820 --> 50:32.530
I'm also a military secret, the Kempeitai are so dumb.

50:32.530 --> 50:35.800
I don't understand anything, but it's still funny.

50:39.350 --> 50:42.930
An happy family, where everyone smiles.

50:43.480 --> 50:44.770
Indeed...

50:44.770 --> 50:45.820
I'm home.

50:46.750 --> 50:49.020
Dad, it was like that right now!

50:50.510 --> 50:52.800
For some reason, I'm not the only one who's funny.

50:50.930 --> 50:54.510
And they asked where her code tables were.

50:54.840 --> 50:57.130
I could hardly restrain myself.

50:59.070 --> 51:04.290
August

50:59.970 --> 51:03.820
The war is on, the cicadas are singing, and the butterflies are flying.

51:04.570 --> 51:06.240
It's so hot.

51:05.250 --> 51:09.980
Attention
Starting in August
The delivery of sugar will stop,
Hurry up to get some

51:08.350 --> 51:10.060
What, there won't be any sugar?

51:11.340 --> 51:17.030
When the air raids began in June, the war seemed to be very close.

51:17.730 --> 51:19.880
Where is she going now?

51:23.420 --> 51:24.710
Ow.

51:24.860 --> 51:26.910
Harumi, I'm sorry.

51:26.910 --> 51:30.200
I'm ok. There are a lot of ants.

51:32.020 --> 51:34.730
I wonder where they all creep to?

51:54.880 --> 51:56.840
SUGAR

51:55.970 --> 51:58.910
Not the sugar, it's too expensive!

52:06.130 --> 52:08.910
We must put it where the ants won't reach it.

52:09.260 --> 52:12.480
Where do we find such a place?

52:16.860 --> 52:18.600
What? What's wrong with you?

52:19.220 --> 52:24.260
We thought that if put it in water,
the ants wouldn't get to it.

52:33.110 --> 52:36.550
Take the money. Go and buy more.

52:40.750 --> 52:42.640
I've never been here before.

52:45.770 --> 52:47.040
Try it.

52:52.420 --> 52:56.770
If there are no products anywhere,
why is there so many people?

53:01.640 --> 53:05.220
Taiwanese rice from old stocks.

53:02.050 --> 53:06.430
Next entry planned
At the end of the month

53:06.570 --> 53:09.350
And then our own local production is no worse.

53:10.330 --> 53:14.150
Wait, aren't watermelons forbidden to grow?

53:16.400 --> 53:18.170
What's this?

53:22.220 --> 53:25.020
It's like it was the summer before the war.

53:26.370 --> 53:28.620
Twenty yen for a kin.

53:26.370 --> 53:28.620
*1 kin = 600 grams

53:29.370 --> 53:31.800
Fifty times more than at the distribution?

53:31.910 --> 53:34.750
Tomorrow, it will become even more expensive.

53:35.020 --> 53:40.240
Mom's money plus this month's living allowance are only 25 yen.

53:40.210 --> 53:43.700
Not buy

53:40.210 --> 53:43.700
buy

53:40.440 --> 53:43.130
Kaki no dance.

53:46.400 --> 53:53.880
If sugar is now about 150 yen, then you can't buy caramel for 100 yen.

53:54.170 --> 53:58.770
Soon it will be a thousand yen just for three pairs of socks.

54:00.080 --> 54:03.600
What will happen to the country, how will it survive?

54:09.220 --> 54:12.620
Wait, where did I get to?

54:13.350 --> 54:16.080
Naganoki? It's behind the military cemetery.

54:16.510 --> 54:18.370
Although, there also Nagasako.

54:18.420 --> 54:19.820
In that direction.

54:20.020 --> 54:21.130
No, over there.

54:36.310 --> 54:37.800
Oh, I'm sorry.

54:42.460 --> 54:43.080
It's nothing.

54:44.200 --> 54:45.110
A watermelon?

54:45.550 --> 54:46.240
Yes.

54:46.600 --> 54:47.620
Caramel?

54:48.150 --> 54:48.930
Yes.

54:49.060 --> 54:50.080
You're lost?

54:50.370 --> 54:51.240
Yes.

54:51.930 --> 54:55.400
And to say you are an adult... Where are you from?

54:55.860 --> 54:56.930
Naganoki.

54:57.860 --> 55:01.530
Sister, no one's telling me the way.

55:01.970 --> 55:06.640
And then everyone is smiling instead, maybe I'm in a fairy tale?

55:07.110 --> 55:12.530
Naganoki, it's right past the post office, and then...

55:13.400 --> 55:14.480
Wait here.

55:16.170 --> 55:18.800
Sister, can I leave?

55:23.800 --> 55:26.280
From this point, you go straight over there.

55:26.400 --> 55:29.930
And then behind the post office, you go right two time and then straight ahead.

55:30.620 --> 55:32.310
Thank you so much!

55:33.440 --> 55:36.750
No one here knows the city well.

55:37.110 --> 55:41.200
Almost everyone are from different places and never leave the district.

55:41.770 --> 55:45.860
You don't look like you're from Hiroshima... maybe from the coast?

55:46.280 --> 55:48.550
Yeah from over there. How do you know?

55:48.800 --> 55:49.800
Your accent.

55:51.150 --> 55:52.000
Are you from Eba?

55:52.220 --> 55:54.130
No, from Kusatsu.

55:54.130 --> 55:55.310
Kusatsu!

55:56.260 --> 55:59.260
I went there every year to see my grandmother and eat watermelon.

55:59.800 --> 56:04.660
Our family was poor, I only got watermelon's skins.

56:05.200 --> 56:10.620
Although, one time, some good people gave me a taste of the core.

56:11.350 --> 56:13.130
That was a long time ago.

56:14.110 --> 56:16.440
Maybe you could draw something for me?

56:16.860 --> 56:20.280
For something to remember... here...

56:21.220 --> 56:22.600
As easy as pie.

56:23.040 --> 56:24.950
I can draw anything, just say it.

56:25.420 --> 56:27.420
Mint candies! Ferns cookies!

56:27.680 --> 56:29.150
Mint...

56:29.330 --> 56:33.550
Ice cream in a waffle cone.

56:33.820 --> 56:34.770
A waffle cone?

56:35.020 --> 56:38.310
You don't know?
You never went to a café?

56:39.000 --> 56:41.370
Enough time off already!

56:41.510 --> 56:43.530
I'm sorry, I have to go.

56:44.820 --> 56:46.550
I'll draw you something the next time.

56:48.510 --> 56:52.600
No. You shouldn't come here again.

56:56.000 --> 56:58.200
You'll get lost again.

57:19.260 --> 57:24.200
You were gone a long time.
I thought you got lost in the city.

57:25.370 --> 57:31.860
Sister, do you know what's an ice cream in a waffle cone?

57:32.020 --> 57:33.680
You don't know?

57:34.280 --> 57:35.790
Oh you.

57:35.790 --> 57:40.750
It's sweet and cold, with a crispy shell, the best dessert.

57:41.000 --> 57:42.710
Ah, there was a time...

57:43.530 --> 57:44.370
There...

57:47.570 --> 57:53.040
Just remembering something that delicious is making simple water seems sweeter.

57:56.360 --> 58:02.660
September

58:00.130 --> 58:01.640
The heat isn't subsiding.

58:03.240 --> 58:06.800
Mrs. Hojo, you have a phone call.

58:07.950 --> 58:10.460
What? For me?

58:14.040 --> 58:15.460
Ah, here it is.

58:16.660 --> 58:18.240
It's so hot.

58:18.240 --> 58:21.800
So you're going to go like that?
Are you not ashamed?

58:32.110 --> 58:34.020
Let's take a walk, it's not that far.

58:34.510 --> 58:37.800
Well, how are things with the police?

58:37.880 --> 58:39.330
Without incident.

58:39.330 --> 58:42.060
Good. Well then, you can...

58:58.400 --> 59:01.710
Shūsaku, I brought your notebook.

59:02.110 --> 59:02.800
Eh?

59:06.800 --> 59:08.420
Ah, Suzu!

59:09.260 --> 59:11.200
You're so pale, are you well?

59:12.130 --> 59:13.800
What? I look strange?

59:14.860 --> 59:16.860
No, you look all right.

59:17.510 --> 59:18.860
Let's go.

59:19.620 --> 59:21.480
Eh? What about work?

59:21.970 --> 59:25.150
I deliberately left the notebook at home so I could be free.

59:26.330 --> 59:29.170
You said you wanted to go shopping.

59:33.440 --> 59:34.350
What are you doing?

59:34.770 --> 59:35.860
You're sure you're ok?

59:36.240 --> 59:38.310
It's my turn to burst out laughing.

59:44.200 --> 59:46.220
I thought I'd take you to the movies.

59:48.600 --> 59:51.510
But then a big ship came to port.

59:53.660 --> 59:58.480
We'll have to give up, but we'll go some other time.

01:00:01.660 --> 01:00:02.530
Suzu?

01:00:03.310 --> 01:00:07.600
Many of my former classmates are now in the Navy.

01:00:08.560 --> 01:00:10.840
What if I see one of them?

01:00:11.060 --> 01:00:13.460
You just greet them normally.

01:00:14.350 --> 01:00:21.130
If I meet someone I know from the past, he could wake me up from my dream.

01:00:21.680 --> 01:00:22.420
Your dream?

01:00:22.750 --> 01:00:26.480
I have a different name and address, and not an easy and simple life.

01:00:27.020 --> 01:00:29.840
But you've always been kind to me.

01:00:30.310 --> 01:00:31.640
And a good friend too.

01:00:32.800 --> 01:00:35.460
I don't want to wake up right now.

01:00:36.240 --> 01:00:39.260
If this is the real me, then so much the better.

01:00:39.350 --> 01:00:40.510
I see.

01:00:41.820 --> 01:00:44.510
Past events, unselected paths.

01:00:45.130 --> 01:00:47.710
They are all like broken dreams.

01:00:48.710 --> 01:00:53.840
Suzu, for me, the best reality is the one in which I chose you.

01:00:55.880 --> 01:00:58.660
You're so skinny, I'm worried.

01:00:59.480 --> 01:01:03.480
You know, I felt hungry in the last few days.

01:01:10.440 --> 01:01:12.110
Here, double scoop.

01:01:17.010 --> 01:01:19.010
HOSPITAL

01:01:19.480 --> 01:01:23.530
You ate a lot in the morning, now that's enough.

01:01:25.820 --> 01:01:27.420
Great, back to the usual portion.

01:01:28.160 --> 01:01:34.460
December

01:01:38.350 --> 01:01:40.110
I'll go ask first.

01:01:40.350 --> 01:01:40.800
Okay.

01:01:42.420 --> 01:01:46.820
Who's there? Wow, a real sailor!

01:01:48.330 --> 01:01:51.240
I went out for water, and we accidentally met.

01:01:51.710 --> 01:01:54.730
I'm Mizuhara Tetsu, a sailor from the ship Aoba.

01:01:55.620 --> 01:01:58.020
The Aoba is a heavy cruiser.

01:01:58.660 --> 01:02:00.110
Behave, Harumi.

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:06.460
It's winter right now and he's tan.

01:02:06.570 --> 01:02:10.040
So, would you like to wash up with us?

01:02:10.240 --> 01:02:13.000
We were given some free time for washing up.

01:02:13.620 --> 01:02:18.480
I didn't know where to go, but I remembered Suzu and decided to ask around for her.

01:02:19.080 --> 01:02:21.680
Thank you for taking care of her.

01:02:22.800 --> 01:02:26.510
Suzu used to draw skillfully and harvest nori.

01:02:26.880 --> 01:02:28.800
There's probably no benefit from her.

01:02:29.440 --> 01:02:33.370
So just ask, and I'll take her back.

01:02:38.220 --> 01:02:42.080
Don't be insolent! "Suzu-Suzu"...
Did I allow you to call me that?

01:02:43.550 --> 01:02:45.280
And how should I call you?

01:02:45.640 --> 01:02:47.280
You're not Urano anymore.

01:02:47.570 --> 01:02:48.220
Eh?

01:02:48.680 --> 01:02:51.400
Suzu, don't be rude to our guest.

01:03:01.350 --> 01:03:02.750
What's so funny?

01:03:03.040 --> 01:03:04.260
It's interesting.

01:03:04.510 --> 01:03:06.370
You're so ordinary.

01:03:06.770 --> 01:03:08.840
It's delicious! Delicious!

01:03:08.910 --> 01:03:10.260
Eat for health.

01:03:10.440 --> 01:03:12.350
This is heaven.

01:03:12.660 --> 01:03:14.910
Suzu, will you rub my back?

01:03:15.060 --> 01:03:16.060
Idiot!

01:03:16.570 --> 01:03:18.820
Suzu, where's the light bulb?

01:03:19.350 --> 01:03:21.710
I think it's in the table drawer.

01:03:21.840 --> 01:03:22.550
I see.

01:03:24.020 --> 01:03:26.680
When I grow up, I'll also become a sailor.

01:03:27.370 --> 01:03:29.000
That's our thing.

01:03:29.000 --> 01:03:29.800
Drink.

01:03:30.330 --> 01:03:31.280
Thanks for the treat.

01:03:31.820 --> 01:03:32.860
Best regards.

01:03:33.110 --> 01:03:34.510
Good night.

01:03:35.350 --> 01:03:36.620
Good night.

01:03:38.910 --> 01:03:40.570
It's a good thing.

01:03:40.800 --> 01:03:42.420
Well, I'm going too.

01:03:43.200 --> 01:03:45.600
How's the Aoba now?

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:49.220
We were damaged in Manila,
we managed to crawl back for repairs.

01:03:49.660 --> 01:03:54.000
She's a good ship. She's still afloat after everything that happened.

01:03:56.200 --> 01:04:01.820
Shūsaku, when everyone die around you, It's haunting to still be alive.

01:04:03.550 --> 01:04:08.660
Mizuhara, my father isn't here tonight and I'm in charge.

01:04:09.370 --> 01:04:13.040
I'm sorry, but I'm not letting you stay in the house.

01:04:18.820 --> 01:04:20.770
He's going to sleep in the barn's attic.

01:04:21.370 --> 01:04:25.800
And you're harsh with him.
I haven't seen you like this before.

01:04:27.600 --> 01:04:30.860
Here, the bed-stove. Bring it to him.

01:04:31.330 --> 01:04:34.910
Talk to him tonight, there may not be another time.

01:04:50.370 --> 01:04:52.310
I'm sorry about the barn.

01:04:53.530 --> 01:04:55.770
After the hanging beds, this is paradise.

01:04:56.310 --> 01:05:00.310
Here, it will warm you up while we talk.

01:05:00.440 --> 01:05:01.240
Okay.

01:05:05.260 --> 01:05:07.530
Here, this is for you.

01:05:07.770 --> 01:05:08.570
Really?

01:05:11.570 --> 01:05:12.820
Do you want to write with it?

01:05:12.860 --> 01:05:13.260
Yes.

01:05:15.330 --> 01:05:16.060
Just like that.

01:05:24.640 --> 01:05:25.930
It's working!

01:05:24.880 --> 01:05:25.820
It's working.

01:05:27.110 --> 01:05:31.400
A bird that looked like a heron flew over us in the middle of the ocean.

01:05:31.860 --> 01:05:34.020
Herons can fly over the ocean.

01:05:34.370 --> 01:05:35.240
Exactly.

01:05:35.910 --> 01:05:39.510
In Eba, they live near the river all year round.

01:05:40.220 --> 01:05:42.910
Yes, there's really a lot in Eba.

01:05:44.570 --> 01:05:47.130
It seems I forgot how to draw them.

01:05:48.280 --> 01:05:50.000
Even you don't always get out?

01:05:51.460 --> 01:05:54.840
It's been a long time since you painted?

01:05:55.150 --> 01:05:55.930
Yeah.

01:05:58.020 --> 01:06:01.060
Remember those rabbits on the waves?

01:06:02.820 --> 01:06:03.550
I remember.

01:06:04.570 --> 01:06:06.660
Oh, and there were problems with them.

01:06:07.200 --> 01:06:09.170
Eh? Why is that?

01:06:10.260 --> 01:06:11.260
You don't remember?

01:06:12.260 --> 01:06:18.370
The teacher sent that drawing to the city competition, and it managed to take a prize.

01:06:18.950 --> 01:06:24.060
But I didn't draw it, imagine how awkward I was.

01:06:24.820 --> 01:06:28.600
It was you that was supposed to win.

01:06:37.200 --> 01:06:42.820
Suzu, you're so warm, so soft, you smell like...

01:06:47.110 --> 01:06:48.150
Mizuhara.

01:06:49.800 --> 01:06:52.860
It think I waited a long time for this day to come.

01:06:54.150 --> 01:06:59.570
You came back like this... wanting to be so close to me!

01:07:00.020 --> 01:07:06.620
How can I... Ah! Now I'm angry with you!

01:07:07.510 --> 01:07:10.440
I'm sorry, really sorry.

01:07:11.710 --> 01:07:15.110
Do you love your husband?

01:07:15.800 --> 01:07:16.550
Yes.

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:21.200
You're still so ordinary.

01:07:21.570 --> 01:07:22.170
Sorry.

01:07:22.330 --> 01:07:27.110
You get angry when you're supposed to be.
Sorry about that.

01:07:28.200 --> 01:07:30.080
So, you don't want me to pick you up?

01:07:30.620 --> 01:07:33.460
You were forced to leave for him, it doesn't matter?

01:07:33.950 --> 01:07:34.550
No.

01:07:35.330 --> 01:07:36.550
Well, that's good.

01:07:39.060 --> 01:07:40.860
He's four years older?

01:07:41.600 --> 01:07:42.600
Shūsaku?

01:07:42.930 --> 01:07:45.080
He's the age of my drowned brother.

01:07:46.510 --> 01:07:51.350
We were poor, so my brother had to go to the nautical school.

01:07:51.950 --> 01:07:54.970
He died, and I took his place.

01:07:55.950 --> 01:07:58.000
That's the way it is.

01:07:58.000 --> 01:08:02.220
But somewhere, I turned off the road laid ahead for an ordinary person.

01:08:03.620 --> 01:08:04.420
But...

01:08:05.310 --> 01:08:08.020
I'm relieved that you live a normal life.

01:08:08.910 --> 01:08:11.440
If I die, don't pray for me.

01:08:12.220 --> 01:08:15.330
Just remember me and smile.

01:08:16.569 --> 01:08:22.260
I just wish you'd been at the end of road of the most ordinary man in the world.

01:08:23.080 --> 01:08:23.819
Suzu!

01:08:23.950 --> 01:08:24.529
What?

01:08:24.529 --> 01:08:25.880
You have become a beauty.

01:08:26.750 --> 01:08:27.970
Don't be foolish!

01:08:30.859 --> 01:08:37.359
In fact, since childhood, it was hard for me to find the right words for you.

01:08:31.649 --> 01:08:38.670
Tetsu
Thank you for the feather.
Thank you for growing up as a worthy person.
Come back alive and healthy.
Suzu.

01:08:38.700 --> 01:08:43.200
The remains of the deceased warrior Miyamoto Teru

01:08:38.700 --> 01:08:43.200
The remains of the deceased warrior Kawauti Tahai

01:08:38.700 --> 01:08:43.200
The remains of the lost warrior Urano Yoichi

01:08:40.760 --> 01:08:46.510
February

01:08:48.680 --> 01:08:50.640
Welcome back, brother.

01:08:51.220 --> 01:08:55.149
There was a pebble instead of dust in the box.

01:08:55.660 --> 01:08:57.729
It was so small and smooth.

01:08:57.729 --> 01:08:59.970
Is that a piece of his skull?

01:09:00.880 --> 01:09:02.529
Maybe it's not him?

01:09:02.880 --> 01:09:04.640
Then what happened to him?

01:09:05.680 --> 01:09:08.130
And why was it necessary to convoke everyone in such a cold weather?

01:09:08.439 --> 01:09:10.970
Our Yoichi could not have died so easily.

01:09:12.279 --> 01:09:14.600
People are so fragile.

01:09:15.149 --> 01:09:19.710
I can't remember his face, not even his voice.

01:09:21.950 --> 01:09:22.840
Shūsaku.

01:09:24.569 --> 01:09:27.750
Thank you for that time.

01:09:29.220 --> 01:09:32.479
When you let me talk to Mizuhara.

01:09:33.710 --> 01:09:34.529
My pleasure.

01:09:35.370 --> 01:09:38.859
However, Shūsaku, you trust our couple to this degree?

01:09:40.950 --> 01:09:43.970
I made you leave for me.

01:09:46.200 --> 01:09:49.660
And didn't even notice that you were angry.

01:09:51.399 --> 01:09:52.910
And you're not noticing now?

01:09:54.860 --> 01:09:57.450
Ooooh. Are you angry now?

01:09:57.620 --> 01:09:59.660
You just don't care!

01:09:59.970 --> 01:10:00.880
Ooooh.

01:10:02.730 --> 01:10:05.950
Then why are you wearing a leaky socks today?

01:10:06.570 --> 01:10:10.130
You gave them to me, so I put them on.

01:10:10.130 --> 01:10:11.350
They were different!

01:10:11.570 --> 01:10:15.350
Listen, can you fight at home?

01:10:16.860 --> 01:10:19.570
Are you confusing the road again? This way.

01:10:19.260 --> 01:10:20.620
I know.

01:10:21.240 --> 01:10:24.350
To the right. In the direction of Mount Higamine.

01:10:24.570 --> 01:10:25.640
Yes, I know!

01:10:29.350 --> 01:10:35.330
A lot of snow fell this winter and spring was delayed.

01:10:36.640 --> 01:10:48.530
♪ Just look, snowflakes fly straight from the sky.

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:42.380
March 19

01:10:48.820 --> 01:11:00.400
♪ Like thousands of tiny white roses, they fall down.

01:11:01.170 --> 01:11:06.370
Come on, you're so obedient, the teacher won't scold you.

01:11:07.200 --> 01:11:10.200
Really? Is it scary at school?

01:11:10.200 --> 01:11:10.680
Not at all.

01:11:11.080 --> 01:11:12.840
You don't have any friends here.

01:11:13.080 --> 01:11:16.750
For example, when I moved here, I was all alone.

01:11:16.950 --> 01:11:19.350
And now I made friends with everyone.

01:11:20.130 --> 01:11:21.530
And with my mom too?

01:12:13.750 --> 01:12:14.880
Put your hood on.

01:12:16.570 --> 01:12:17.440
Harumi!

01:12:40.550 --> 01:12:43.440
It's like paint on a large canvas.

01:12:44.440 --> 01:12:48.170
What am I thinking about?

01:12:50.770 --> 01:12:54.570
What are you standing there for?
Lie down and press against the wall.

01:12:55.770 --> 01:12:56.680
Welcome back.

01:12:59.400 --> 01:13:02.130
Yeah, it's a good time to be welcome.

01:13:03.130 --> 01:13:05.730
Be careful, shards can get here.

01:13:20.240 --> 01:13:21.000
Ow!

01:13:24.150 --> 01:13:26.420
Just listen.

01:13:26.420 --> 01:13:27.020
Eh?

01:13:27.370 --> 01:13:30.840
This sound of our engines is 2000 horsepower.

01:13:31.750 --> 01:13:37.350
We worked day and night in the factory to improve them.

01:13:39.750 --> 01:13:43.970
We started with the usual type-95, with a capacity of only 500 horsepower.

01:13:46.260 --> 01:13:51.440
New technologies and hard work.

01:13:52.640 --> 01:13:56.560
For the sake of eternal peace and prosperity.

01:13:59.130 --> 01:14:03.290
We spare no effort...

01:14:02.550 --> 01:14:05.400
What's the horse power of our enemies?

01:14:07.550 --> 01:14:10.150
Say, the horse power of our enemies?

01:14:10.710 --> 01:14:11.710
Dad!

01:14:16.440 --> 01:14:20.280
The raid is over!

01:14:23.930 --> 01:14:26.660
He worked night shift relentlessly.

01:14:26.930 --> 01:14:31.000
And during the raid, he just laid down on the ground and fell asleep.

01:14:32.420 --> 01:14:34.310
I was so scared!

01:14:34.440 --> 01:14:37.170
After the raid, we collected a lot of dead fish.

01:14:37.350 --> 01:14:38.480
Small!

01:14:38.930 --> 01:14:42.040
And you draw a big one, and it will become bigger.

01:14:44.790 --> 01:14:50.840
04:50
March 29

01:14:47.840 --> 01:14:49.750
Air alarm! Air alarm!

01:14:49.950 --> 01:14:52.080
Put your hood on, put out the lights.

01:14:52.280 --> 01:14:53.860
Remove the paper doors.

01:14:54.060 --> 01:14:57.620
Take the essentials and go to the shelter.

01:14:59.130 --> 01:15:03.040
The raid is over!

01:15:04.480 --> 01:15:07.260
It's not cooked at all.

01:15:06.790 --> 01:15:08.800
Japanese
 Imperial
 Women's union

01:15:07.350 --> 01:15:12.320
March 31

01:15:07.440 --> 01:15:09.440
What a pain.

01:15:09.600 --> 01:15:15.060
Her husband and elder brother were killed in the war, now they are taking their son to the army.

01:15:15.280 --> 01:15:17.060
Congratulations.

01:15:20.620 --> 01:15:25.580
1 April
22h10

01:15:21.840 --> 01:15:23.350
Wear your protective hood.

01:15:23.400 --> 01:15:24.570
Extinguish the lights.

01:15:24.570 --> 01:15:26.080
Remove the paper doors.

01:15:26.420 --> 01:15:27.370
Set the Fire-fighting...

01:15:28.550 --> 01:15:31.040
You can't see a thing.

01:15:31.040 --> 01:15:31.680
Ay.

01:15:32.950 --> 01:15:34.150
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:15:34.440 --> 01:15:36.110
Whose cat is this?

01:15:42.310 --> 01:15:44.310
How many alerts is it?

01:15:58.640 --> 01:16:00.200
It's the first time I see this.

01:16:07.040 --> 01:16:11.250
April 6

01:16:12.080 --> 01:16:16.970
10:43. Heavy bombers are coming from Tokuyama.

01:16:13.960 --> 01:16:19.170
May 5

01:16:17.280 --> 01:16:18.640
Tokuyama is launching.

01:16:18.820 --> 01:16:25.240
Thirty targets seen in the southeast of Tokushima prefecture are moving towards Kure.

01:16:26.970 --> 01:16:30.730
The raid is over!

01:16:32.480 --> 01:16:36.440
More than 125 B-29 bombers participated in the raid.

01:16:36.820 --> 01:16:41.660
Hiro's naval arsenal suffered serious damage.

01:16:40.040 --> 01:16:41.110
I'm home.

01:16:42.080 --> 01:16:44.750
But the number of casualties is minimal.

01:16:42.710 --> 01:16:44.640
Are you okay, Shūsaku?

01:16:44.710 --> 01:16:45.730
And father?

01:16:46.800 --> 01:16:48.240
He didn't come back.

01:16:48.530 --> 01:16:49.330
I see.

01:16:53.280 --> 01:16:55.510
Suzu, put out the fire.

01:17:05.000 --> 01:17:07.220
Suzu, you're so small.

01:17:09.600 --> 01:17:10.240
What?

01:17:10.510 --> 01:17:12.680
You're still small.

01:17:13.860 --> 01:17:15.060
So what?

01:17:15.260 --> 01:17:16.240
Nothing.

01:17:16.880 --> 01:17:18.800
I'm just telling you the truth.

01:17:31.860 --> 01:17:34.860
Dad's going to be fine.

01:17:34.860 --> 01:17:35.910
There's a uniform.

01:17:36.200 --> 01:17:36.710
Eh?

01:17:37.730 --> 01:17:39.020
In that package.

01:17:40.550 --> 01:17:43.840
Starting the 15th, we're becoming part of the army.

01:17:44.660 --> 01:17:48.110
I'm a soldier now, and I am going to exercise with the fleet.

01:17:48.480 --> 01:17:49.880
I won't be here for three months.

01:17:51.110 --> 01:17:54.080
But then you'll come back?

01:17:54.310 --> 01:17:55.110
Probably.

01:17:56.400 --> 01:17:58.330
Are you going to be okay, Suzu?

01:17:59.130 --> 01:18:01.110
You're so small and skinny.

01:18:01.530 --> 01:18:05.660
If there are no men left to hold the fort, will you be able to protect it?

01:18:06.620 --> 01:18:07.510
No.

01:18:08.550 --> 01:18:09.600
No way!

01:18:15.600 --> 01:18:18.000
I'm sorry, that's not true.

01:18:19.350 --> 01:18:20.770
I love you.

01:18:21.820 --> 01:18:25.880
But in three months, I'm going to forget your face.

01:18:26.710 --> 01:18:27.730
Suzu.

01:18:28.150 --> 01:18:30.040
I'll be waiting for you in this house.

01:18:30.620 --> 01:18:34.620
If it's not there, I might not find you.

01:18:36.100 --> 01:18:39.980
May 6
Sunday.

01:18:39.480 --> 01:18:41.780
May 8
Tuesday.

01:18:42.440 --> 01:18:48.320
May 10.
Thursday.
Air alarm.

01:18:43.740 --> 01:18:48.320
May 11.
Friday.
Two alarms
in the morning.

01:18:44.860 --> 01:18:48.320
May 12.
Saturday.
There was no alarm.

01:18:46.150 --> 01:18:48.320
May 13.
Sunday.
Only a siren
three times.

01:18:49.070 --> 01:18:54.580
May 14

01:18:54.440 --> 01:18:56.310
And now you won't forget?

01:18:56.460 --> 01:18:59.060
It was just a saying.

01:18:59.330 --> 01:19:01.640
No, not in your case.

01:19:02.000 --> 01:19:04.660
Let me see how you drew me.

01:19:04.660 --> 01:19:05.710
No way.

01:19:06.000 --> 01:19:07.950
This is a military secret.

01:19:12.350 --> 01:19:17.600
May 15

01:19:22.420 --> 01:19:24.280
Well, I'm leaving.

01:19:25.860 --> 01:19:26.770
Have a safe trip.

01:19:28.220 --> 01:19:30.840
Shūsaku, you and I are on our way.

01:19:30.840 --> 01:19:31.330
Yes.

01:19:32.240 --> 01:19:34.170
You've become a real sailor.

01:19:36.330 --> 01:19:40.130
The house just became completely empty.

01:19:41.710 --> 01:19:46.590
June 21

01:19:45.310 --> 01:19:46.400
For Ms. Hojo!

01:19:47.620 --> 01:19:49.590
Hiroshima Prefecture, Kure, Upper Naganoki, 808

01:19:53.840 --> 01:19:56.660
He was supposed to get to the factory hospital.

01:19:57.130 --> 01:19:58.110
Wow...

01:19:58.330 --> 01:20:00.400
That's why they couldn't find him.

01:20:00.910 --> 01:20:05.440
Dad was wounded in the stomach and on the head, but he's almost recovered.

01:20:07.310 --> 01:20:09.910
I'll take his watch for repairs.

01:20:10.910 --> 01:20:17.060
This is a rare occasion to see the Kuromura in Simonoseki for a short while. I'll go tomorrow.

01:20:18.370 --> 01:20:20.040
To the place where brother lives?

01:20:20.170 --> 01:20:21.350
I'm going.

01:20:21.880 --> 01:20:22.620
Will you take me?

01:20:25.110 --> 01:20:26.060
Is this a school?

01:20:26.110 --> 01:20:29.860
It's a school. But now there's only gymnastics in there.

01:20:42.710 --> 01:20:44.350
It's going to take a long time.

01:20:45.550 --> 01:20:49.770
While I'm buying a ticket, can you and Harumi go see Papa at the hospital?

01:20:50.640 --> 01:20:53.350
All right, come with me, Harumi.

01:20:53.460 --> 01:20:55.350
We'll go see the fleet base?

01:20:55.770 --> 01:20:56.370
Yes.

01:20:59.480 --> 01:21:00.950
Why are you frowning?

01:21:01.130 --> 01:21:03.930
They make the best bamboo spears in the world over there.

01:21:04.110 --> 01:21:07.110
Are you stupid? My husband's parents are terrible people.

01:21:07.840 --> 01:21:10.480
Just seeing you like this is unusual...

01:21:10.480 --> 01:21:12.930
And what should I do with a bamboo spear?

01:21:13.060 --> 01:21:15.220
Is Simonosaki far?

01:21:15.330 --> 01:21:15.950
Yes.

01:21:16.350 --> 01:21:18.150
Next to Hiroshima?

01:21:18.220 --> 01:21:19.480
Much farther.

01:21:19.480 --> 01:21:20.310
That way?

01:21:20.600 --> 01:21:22.910
Here's the hospital, be quiet.

01:21:28.060 --> 01:21:29.950
They're listening to enemy songs?

01:21:30.330 --> 01:21:32.110
I made you worry.

01:21:32.550 --> 01:21:36.570
I was unconscious all the time until June.

01:21:36.570 --> 01:21:38.240
What's important is that you're alive.

01:21:38.710 --> 01:21:41.970
And now we will take the train and go see my brother.

01:21:42.150 --> 01:21:44.910
Are you? Well, the sooner, the better.

01:21:45.040 --> 01:21:47.750
Uncle, what ship are you from?

01:21:48.000 --> 01:21:50.150
From mine trawler number 16.

01:21:52.530 --> 01:21:55.770
I've learned a lot of news over here.

01:21:56.220 --> 01:21:57.980
Hiro's arsenal has been destroyed.

01:21:58.220 --> 01:22:02.020
The whole fleet wants to be transferred to the army command.

01:22:02.660 --> 01:22:05.860
Suzu, they sunk the Yamato.

01:22:05.860 --> 01:22:06.730
The Yamato?

01:22:07.110 --> 01:22:07.970
Yes.

01:22:08.130 --> 01:22:11.970
She moved in front of the fleet, diverting enemies onto herself.

01:22:13.000 --> 01:22:16.910
The inner Sea of Japan now belongs to the enemy.

01:22:17.310 --> 01:22:20.600
So the rabbits are on the waves now...

01:22:20.880 --> 01:22:22.460
Really? Really?

01:22:20.910 --> 01:22:21.660
What?

01:22:22.080 --> 01:22:22.680
Nothing.

01:22:22.950 --> 01:22:25.060
I would advise the same.

01:22:25.880 --> 01:22:29.860
Harumi should be sent to her father's family.

01:22:30.200 --> 01:22:32.370
It'll be much safer there.

01:22:33.840 --> 01:22:35.150
What about sister...

01:22:35.570 --> 01:22:36.570
Listen, Suzu.

01:22:36.660 --> 01:22:37.130
Yes?

01:22:37.280 --> 01:22:38.620
Let's see from over there?

01:22:38.800 --> 01:22:42.110
I'll tell my brother what ships we have here.

01:22:42.460 --> 01:22:44.310
I can't see anything.

01:22:44.680 --> 01:22:46.530
Let's keep going. Let's keep going.

01:22:47.110 --> 01:22:48.080
I can't see.

01:22:51.080 --> 01:22:52.880
There's trouble, what to do?

01:22:53.150 --> 01:22:56.400
We don't have time to get back home.
There should be a public shelter somewhere.

01:22:58.460 --> 01:22:59.820
Is there really something flying?

01:23:00.110 --> 01:23:02.770
They usually just try to scare us and fly away.

01:23:03.420 --> 01:23:11.330
09:23. North-east of Tokuyama, enemy aircrafts going towards Kure.

01:23:13.910 --> 01:23:15.440
Looks like the really are flying.

01:23:15.530 --> 01:23:17.620
Excuse me, can we come with you?

01:23:17.820 --> 01:23:18.820
Come in.

01:23:19.020 --> 01:23:21.910
Red alert! Faster!

01:23:25.930 --> 01:23:27.600
Suzu, I'm afraid.

01:23:27.600 --> 01:23:29.800
Don't worry, look.

01:23:33.060 --> 01:23:33.880
Mama?

01:23:33.910 --> 01:23:36.020
Yes, and who is this?

01:23:36.950 --> 01:23:37.880
Harumi?

01:23:38.220 --> 01:23:40.550
Here you are with your mother.

01:23:40.770 --> 01:23:42.800
You must be from afar.

01:23:43.220 --> 01:23:45.880
We're here to visit the hospital. From Naganoki.

01:23:46.020 --> 01:23:48.170
You're out of luck.

01:23:48.680 --> 01:23:51.820
Here they are! Close your ears, open your mouth, bend your head!

01:23:53.710 --> 01:23:54.730
It's hot.

01:23:55.550 --> 01:23:56.330
Bend down.

01:24:30.310 --> 01:24:33.240
Excuse me, can we have some water?

01:24:34.110 --> 01:24:34.770
Yes.

01:24:39.240 --> 01:24:40.910
Thank you very much.

01:24:42.000 --> 01:24:44.750
We're not too late for the train?

01:24:45.570 --> 01:24:48.260
The train couldn't leave, it waiting for us.

01:24:57.660 --> 01:24:59.020
I can't see anything!

01:25:01.730 --> 01:25:03.710
Are you okay over there?

01:25:03.800 --> 01:25:04.970
Yes!

01:25:05.150 --> 01:25:11.310
It's dangerous to stand there. There
could be unexploded bombs. Go away.

01:25:12.020 --> 01:25:15.280
What? Thank you for your work!

01:25:15.530 --> 01:25:20.130
Say, Suzu, are you going to draw my brother?

01:25:20.860 --> 01:25:23.420
Craters from unexploded bombs are not large.

01:25:23.510 --> 01:25:26.660
According to the latest civil defense reports,

01:25:26.910 --> 01:25:29.370
Part of the bombs dropped by the enemy...

01:25:31.000 --> 01:25:32.730
Let's go, Harumi!

01:26:09.240 --> 01:26:11.770
Okay, here we go again. Not like that.

01:26:12.060 --> 01:26:15.240
No one's will ever get married to you like that.

01:26:15.860 --> 01:26:21.770
I think I've been told this a lot, but I'm already married.

01:26:23.910 --> 01:26:24.770
Watermelon.

01:26:26.000 --> 01:26:27.240
Ferns biscuits.

01:26:28.440 --> 01:26:29.730
Mint candies.

01:26:30.620 --> 01:26:35.460
If the road had a ditch, we could have hidden in it.

01:26:36.510 --> 01:26:39.330
In my left hand, things.

01:26:40.440 --> 01:26:42.140
In my right hand, Harumi.

01:26:43.620 --> 01:26:46.150
If it were the other way around.

01:26:47.910 --> 01:26:51.280
I could have thrown off my sandals and ran.

01:26:52.710 --> 01:26:56.480
Further down the slope, to the other side...

01:26:57.240 --> 01:27:00.220
This is the Tone, and that one's the Hyuga.

01:27:01.370 --> 01:27:04.240
Mom, this is the Yamato.

01:27:07.530 --> 01:27:14.640
She... she looks so much like Shuusaku.

01:27:16.040 --> 01:27:20.750
I should have followed... I really should have followed you...

01:27:21.880 --> 01:27:24.860
I'm sorry. Forgive me, Harumi.

01:27:25.370 --> 01:27:26.860
I'm sorry, sister.

01:27:26.860 --> 01:27:28.530
Murderer!

01:27:29.480 --> 01:27:31.310
Murderer!

01:27:31.310 --> 01:27:32.770
Don't, Keiko.

01:27:32.000 --> 01:27:33.730
Give me back Harumi!!

01:27:33.540 --> 01:27:35.420
The tofu distribution will begin soon.

01:27:37.220 --> 01:27:41.680
She's grieving, don't let it go in your head.

01:27:42.200 --> 01:27:47.040
It is good that at least you are alive.

01:27:48.040 --> 01:27:48.930
Really?

01:27:49.970 --> 01:27:54.510
There's a place for everyone in this world.

01:27:54.510 --> 01:27:55.310
Rin.

01:27:55.310 --> 01:27:55.840
Yes?

01:27:56.910 --> 01:28:00.620
And then? Where was my cherished place?

01:28:01.730 --> 01:28:05.400
In that fence there could have been a broken board.

01:28:06.440 --> 01:28:08.840
And the wind from the explosion would have carried us.

01:28:09.950 --> 01:28:13.170
Far, far from there.

01:28:13.970 --> 01:28:18.350
June 28

01:28:15.600 --> 01:28:17.820
Well, here we are again.

01:28:17.820 --> 01:28:20.460
I can't hear the planes. Keep sleeping.

01:28:21.150 --> 01:28:24.620
Nothing will happen to the house?

01:28:25.310 --> 01:28:28.130
Of course, don't worry.

01:28:28.480 --> 01:28:29.600
I'm glad.

01:28:30.440 --> 01:28:31.280
Liar.

01:28:32.260 --> 01:28:33.310
That woman...

01:28:34.440 --> 01:28:40.550
If our house were broken, I could go away from the city.

01:28:41.290 --> 01:28:45.290
July 1

01:28:43.330 --> 01:28:44.570
Don't force yourself.

01:28:45.350 --> 01:28:49.400
You know, we don't have the time to relax.

01:28:49.510 --> 01:28:50.510
See you later.

01:28:54.200 --> 01:28:56.220
Looks like the Sun came out.

01:28:56.620 --> 01:28:59.330
Let me tie you up.

01:29:02.820 --> 01:29:04.750
The central region's defense reports.

01:29:04.950 --> 01:29:08.520
23:50. Two targets are observed in the bay of Hiroshima.

01:29:08.520 --> 01:29:12.120
There are two targets over the Suo Strait. There is also two more targets above the Bungo Channel.

01:29:09.730 --> 01:29:11.680
Are you awake, Suzu?

01:29:12.120 --> 01:29:14.780
And also in the northeast are seen...

01:29:15.310 --> 01:29:21.110
23:58. A lot of enemy planes are circling over Hiroshima and Kure.

01:29:19.800 --> 01:29:20.510
Like this.

01:29:21.680 --> 01:29:28.150
23:58. A lot of enemy planes are circling over Hiroshima and Kure.

01:29:28.310 --> 01:29:32.510
They say that there are many planes. But you can't even see their shadows.

01:29:36.600 --> 01:29:38.240
Flare bombs?

01:29:42.170 --> 01:29:43.930
Suzu, come with us more quickly.

01:30:04.110 --> 01:30:05.550
Let's get outta here!

01:30:15.770 --> 01:30:18.020
Suzu? Why aren't you coming?

01:30:18.260 --> 01:30:19.330
Hurry up!

01:30:25.040 --> 01:30:27.910
Suzu! Suzu!

01:30:39.130 --> 01:30:41.600
Suzu, why are you staying?

01:30:41.840 --> 01:30:44.260
Water! More water!

01:30:45.930 --> 01:30:47.020
Well, we got it.

01:30:46.310 --> 01:30:48.080
Defense of the central region.

01:30:48.730 --> 01:30:55.460
00:30. The enemy air group flew over the Bungo Channel.

01:30:51.660 --> 01:30:52.510
Careful.

01:30:55.840 --> 01:31:03.080
In addition, one more air group is approaching the Bungo Channel and three more were seen in the southern waters.

01:30:59.040 --> 01:31:00.510
So that's it.

01:31:01.040 --> 01:31:02.880
One-two.

01:31:03.080 --> 01:31:04.260
End of message.

01:31:04.880 --> 01:31:08.350
This is JOFK. The transmitting station of Hiroshima.

01:31:08.350 --> 01:31:10.780
Residents of Kure, hang on!

01:31:11.000 --> 01:31:13.530
Residents of Kure, hang on!

01:31:16.570 --> 01:31:23.950
To the affected inhabitants of Kure, Hiroshima sends rice.

01:31:24.330 --> 01:31:28.210
Distribution will be in Ito Park!

01:31:28.210 --> 01:31:30.420
And where will I get my I.D.?

01:31:30.420 --> 01:31:32.150
The government don't know yet.

01:31:32.150 --> 01:31:34.200
My house burned down.

01:31:33.480 --> 01:31:36.420
They didn't get into the bomb shelter and remained alive.

01:31:35.930 --> 01:31:37.600
Can I get that bandage?

01:31:37.600 --> 01:31:38.950
Take it.

01:31:41.750 --> 01:31:47.640
Here, eat it while it's hot. I kept them in the subfield and they were all baked.

01:31:48.860 --> 01:31:50.110
Thank you.

01:31:50.570 --> 01:31:51.820
And for my sister...

01:31:53.440 --> 01:31:57.170
Oh, the heat, it's so hot.

01:31:57.680 --> 01:32:00.860
Is there anyone from Sinonome?

01:32:00.860 --> 01:32:05.730
There was no fire break in Asahimachi. Almost everything burned out.

01:32:05.840 --> 01:32:06.710
I see.

01:32:08.730 --> 01:32:09.660
Suzu!

01:32:10.170 --> 01:32:13.530
Hey. Are you hurt?

01:32:13.730 --> 01:32:14.910
What about your training?

01:32:14.910 --> 01:32:15.730
They stopped it.

01:32:16.170 --> 01:32:19.060
It's a good thing you're alive.

01:32:20.150 --> 01:32:22.440
And now I suddenly want to sleep.

01:32:22.440 --> 01:32:23.110
Suzu!

01:32:23.420 --> 01:32:29.510
"We'll find a cool place," came to me from somewhere.

01:32:24.000 --> 01:32:24.800
Suzu! What are you doing?

01:32:32.260 --> 01:32:33.660
It's a good thing...

01:32:34.060 --> 01:32:36.480
It's a good thing that she had time to put it out.

01:32:37.570 --> 01:32:39.330
It's a good thing it wasn't a bomb.

01:32:39.330 --> 01:32:41.600
It's a good thing it didn't catch fire.

01:32:41.710 --> 01:32:43.930
It's a good thing that it's healing so quickly.

01:32:44.130 --> 01:32:48.440
Good, good, good...

01:32:49.570 --> 01:32:53.020
I no longer know what is good.

01:32:54.840 --> 01:32:58.150
In June, I held Harumi with my right hand.

01:32:59.080 --> 01:33:02.800
In May, I painted Shūsaku's face with my right hand.

01:33:03.970 --> 01:33:07.950
In April, I took the lipstick with my right hand.

01:33:08.110 --> 01:33:12.200
In February, I held the remains of my brother with my right hand.

01:33:12.750 --> 01:33:17.460
Last November, I accidentally ruined my sister's kimono with my right hand.

01:33:18.400 --> 01:33:22.440
Last August I drew a watermelon for Rin with my right hand.

01:33:20.400 --> 01:33:25.710
Last July, the kempeitai took away the drawing made with my right hand.

01:33:24.000 --> 01:33:27.460
Last May, I cooked Kusunoki's rice recipe with my right hand.

01:33:25.910 --> 01:33:29.710
Last April I tore the dandelions with my right hand.

01:33:29.910 --> 01:33:34.040
Last March I drew my hometown with my right hand.

01:33:31.720 --> 01:33:36.510
Two years ago I collected nori with my right hand.

01:33:37.680 --> 01:33:42.260
Seven years ago in February, I drew rabbits with my right hand.

01:33:44.370 --> 01:33:46.260
Your sister's here.

01:33:46.400 --> 01:33:48.680
What happened to you, Suzu?

01:33:49.730 --> 01:33:50.750
Sumi?

01:33:51.110 --> 01:33:53.310
You came to see me?

01:33:53.310 --> 01:33:58.130
A officer I know let me ride on the truck to help.

01:33:59.600 --> 01:34:00.460
What's that?

01:34:00.660 --> 01:34:01.170
So.

01:34:01.460 --> 01:34:03.880
Here. It's old, but it's pure cotton.

01:34:04.220 --> 01:34:05.750
Without artificial fibers?

01:34:05.820 --> 01:34:07.350
Absolutely.

01:34:21.440 --> 01:34:22.640
Sorry.

01:34:27.280 --> 01:34:31.400
And here's some medlar from Ebayama.

01:34:32.110 --> 01:34:33.350
Can you do that?

01:34:33.710 --> 01:34:37.370
I need to do some stretching. I'll walk you halfway.

01:34:37.570 --> 01:34:40.640
I'm expected not far from the fire station.

01:34:40.770 --> 01:34:43.530
Why not at the observation tower on the river?

01:34:43.880 --> 01:34:46.150
Ah, it's probably burnt.

01:34:46.150 --> 01:34:47.800
It's still in place.

01:34:48.150 --> 01:34:50.950
One officer from Kure showed it to me.

01:34:51.370 --> 01:34:57.280
He's so young and kind, he used to give me coupons for lunch and movie tickets.

01:34:57.530 --> 01:35:02.640
And he remembered that I have a married big sister here.

01:35:02.930 --> 01:35:03.910
Are you in love?

01:35:04.440 --> 01:35:07.640
Oh, what are you talking about, Suzu?

01:35:07.910 --> 01:35:08.750
It hurts.

01:35:10.790 --> 01:35:14.500
Go back to your place and
continue to work. Let's go
to work together. Put all your
hatred in hard work.
To protect your hometown
we need heroic perseverance.
Don't give up!
2 July, Shōwa 20. Kure's City Hall

01:35:10.790 --> 01:35:14.500
Attention
1. Food stocks have been prepared.
2. Emergency centers are fully equipped
3. Distribution of funds for the first
need to start immediately
Kure's City Hall

01:35:12.640 --> 01:35:14.080
This is awful.

01:35:25.820 --> 01:35:30.020
Kure gets bombed endlessly, how do people endure?

01:35:30.860 --> 01:35:35.510
It's so awful when there's no home to return to.

01:35:37.750 --> 01:35:39.060
Listen, Suzu.

01:35:40.080 --> 01:35:42.280
Return with us to Hiroshima.

01:35:42.640 --> 01:35:43.440
Eh?

01:35:43.930 --> 01:35:45.840
It's almost not bombed.

01:35:46.040 --> 01:35:50.260
Brother is no more, no one's going to hurt you.

01:35:53.110 --> 01:35:54.550
It's tempting.

01:35:55.880 --> 01:35:59.800
At the same time I could see if your young officer is really cute.

01:36:00.510 --> 01:36:02.130
It's not fair.

01:36:02.280 --> 01:36:03.310
Yes, I'm joking.

01:36:03.480 --> 01:36:04.660
Bye then.

01:36:04.730 --> 01:36:05.570
I'm skewed.

01:36:05.730 --> 01:36:08.260
Think about it.

01:36:08.950 --> 01:36:13.710
Next month, on the 6th, there will be a festival, come back home.

01:36:13.840 --> 01:36:16.060
Thank you, Sumi.

01:36:16.240 --> 01:36:19.000
I was glad that my brother was dead.

01:36:20.080 --> 01:36:24.730
I'm skewed, like drawings with my left hand.

01:37:10.380 --> 01:37:15.390
28 July
7 am

01:37:13.710 --> 01:37:17.550
Today they are buzzing all day.
We need to take something with us.

01:37:17.550 --> 01:37:18.350
Ouch!

01:37:18.440 --> 01:37:20.750
Suzu, come down here.

01:37:28.710 --> 01:37:29.880
You can't come in here.

01:37:31.640 --> 01:37:33.930
You can't come here now!

01:37:44.310 --> 01:37:47.260
Fly away! Fly away from here!

01:37:47.710 --> 01:37:50.420
Fly away up the mountain! To Hiroshima!

01:38:23.110 --> 01:38:24.200
Are you tired of living?

01:38:25.310 --> 01:38:26.240
Forgive me.

01:38:26.460 --> 01:38:29.550
A heron. A heron flew by.

01:38:31.280 --> 01:38:32.820
It flew away from the sea.

01:38:33.930 --> 01:38:38.480
Shūsaku, I want... to return to Hiroshima.

01:38:43.220 --> 01:38:44.750
And never come back?

01:38:46.440 --> 01:38:47.840
Are you having a hard time without a hand?

01:38:49.130 --> 01:38:50.420
Are you afraid of the attacks?

01:38:51.510 --> 01:38:52.710
Is it because of Harumi?

01:38:52.750 --> 01:38:53.680
That's right.

01:38:54.170 --> 01:38:55.060
That's right.

01:38:55.530 --> 01:38:56.730
So it is.

01:38:57.040 --> 01:38:58.080
I can't hear you!

01:38:58.080 --> 01:38:59.020
Not at all.

01:39:00.710 --> 01:39:02.280
Then why?

01:39:03.930 --> 01:39:07.060
Suzu, I was happy.

01:39:07.620 --> 01:39:10.680
Going back to the house where you are waiting.

01:39:11.420 --> 01:39:14.860
Walking with you through the streets and talking about something.

01:39:16.600 --> 01:39:18.060
Aren't you?

01:39:18.330 --> 01:39:20.260
Were you just pretending?

01:39:23.600 --> 01:39:24.620
I'm not listening.

01:39:25.730 --> 01:39:28.460
I'm not listening, I'm not hearing anything!

01:39:28.570 --> 01:39:31.950
I Want! Home! Back to Hiroshima!

01:39:32.150 --> 01:39:35.600
Is that it? Well, go!

01:39:48.670 --> 01:39:53.090
9 days later

01:39:48.930 --> 01:39:51.710
The enemies of the central region are not seen.

01:39:52.150 --> 01:39:55.000
The enemies of the central region are not seen.

01:39:55.660 --> 01:40:00.880
In Hiroshima prefecture at 07:31 the air alarm is canceled.

01:40:02.620 --> 01:40:04.970
So the alarm has been canceled.

01:40:05.040 --> 01:40:06.860
Well, then we're going.

01:40:06.860 --> 01:40:08.620
Have a safe trip.

01:40:10.240 --> 01:40:12.710
Ow-ow-ow-ow-ow.

01:40:13.420 --> 01:40:14.620
More over there.

01:40:15.040 --> 01:40:17.950
Oh, it's morning, it's already hot.

01:40:20.110 --> 01:40:24.800
It will be lonely in here when Suzu leaves us.

01:40:44.480 --> 01:40:46.710
Say, when do you want to go?

01:40:47.200 --> 01:40:47.550
Eh?

01:40:48.170 --> 01:40:48.910
The hospital.

01:40:49.910 --> 01:40:52.680
Ah... by 10 o'clock.

01:40:56.330 --> 01:40:57.750
You're not going to do that.

01:41:09.440 --> 01:41:10.420
I'm sorry.

01:41:10.640 --> 01:41:11.480
That one...

01:41:12.820 --> 01:41:15.350
It doesn't need to be washed.

01:41:17.440 --> 01:41:20.730
Today, have some free time in town.

01:41:22.020 --> 01:41:25.110
Yes, but I'm leaving at the end of the week.

01:41:25.660 --> 01:41:28.820
Today I need to go to the hospital.

01:41:32.770 --> 01:41:33.950
Don't peek.

01:41:33.950 --> 01:41:34.970
I'm sorry.

01:41:36.440 --> 01:41:38.510
The Hospital can't keep up.

01:41:39.220 --> 01:41:41.170
Our doctor is very busy.

01:41:42.000 --> 01:41:45.800
You can get a doctor's statement in Hiroshima.

01:41:46.620 --> 01:41:49.240
Just don't buy your tickets now.

01:41:51.800 --> 01:41:54.130
Here, a gift from your sister.

01:41:54.730 --> 01:41:56.130
I made some pants.

01:41:57.000 --> 01:41:59.400
I sewed an elastic band so you could wear it by yourself.

01:41:59.510 --> 01:42:01.660
Sorry if it's a little crooked.

01:42:03.570 --> 01:42:05.170
Thank you so much.

01:42:09.170 --> 01:42:13.620
Forgive me, I shouldn't have blamed you for Harumi.

01:42:14.750 --> 01:42:15.660
No problem.

01:42:15.590 --> 01:42:20.930
Kuromura Watchmaker Shop

01:42:17.800 --> 01:42:20.000
I lost my beloved husband early.

01:42:21.150 --> 01:42:23.070
My house got destroyed.

01:42:24.160 --> 01:42:25.970
I couldn't see my son.

01:42:27.240 --> 01:42:29.910
But still, I chose my own path.

01:42:32.040 --> 01:42:36.240
You're different. You obediently moved to an unfamiliar house.

01:42:36.650 --> 01:42:38.560
You do what you're told.

01:42:40.000 --> 01:42:42.680
It must be a very boring life.

01:42:47.620 --> 01:42:51.440
Maybe your cherished place is not here but somewhere else.

01:42:52.020 --> 01:42:54.880
Anyway, it's up to you to decide.

01:43:06.570 --> 01:43:09.440
Keiko, what was that flash?

01:43:09.570 --> 01:43:14.170
I don't know. It's like lightning but there's not a cloud in the sky.

01:43:14.800 --> 01:43:18.840
Still, can you help me wash this dress?

01:43:20.260 --> 01:43:22.570
And yet...

01:43:23.170 --> 01:43:25.620
Can I stay here?

01:43:25.820 --> 01:43:29.510
Yes you can, you can, let me go, it's hot.

01:43:39.110 --> 01:43:40.710
What was that?

01:43:43.200 --> 01:43:46.080
I can't hear anything from JOFK.

01:43:46.120 --> 01:43:47.460
Nothing?

01:43:47.570 --> 01:43:48.480
Hey!

01:43:48.640 --> 01:43:49.170
Yes?

01:43:49.680 --> 01:43:51.220
Come out, take a look!

01:43:55.330 --> 01:43:57.530
What is this cloud?

01:43:59.330 --> 01:43:59.930
Cloud?

01:44:01.330 --> 01:44:04.660
Do you see those huge clouds?
They are called anvils.

01:44:05.530 --> 01:44:12.400
This is Okuyama radio station. Hiroshima Station, respond. This is Okuyama radio station.

01:44:12.660 --> 01:44:17.880
I went to see what had fallen, and this is a transfer board from Hiroshima.

01:44:24.910 --> 01:44:28.680
Everyone who's not busy, go to the district council's building.

01:44:30.370 --> 01:44:32.660
Isn't Tita like a nurse?

01:44:32.800 --> 01:44:35.820
But I've never done it before.

01:44:36.440 --> 01:44:38.530
We've never done this before.

01:44:38.660 --> 01:44:39.950
Is that right?

01:44:39.950 --> 01:44:40.510
Yes.

01:44:42.400 --> 01:44:44.770
It's a shame to only have one hand.

01:44:44.770 --> 01:44:46.440
Are you making fun of me?

01:44:46.730 --> 01:44:49.260
Why do you need all those sandals?

01:44:49.460 --> 01:44:53.420
We'll take them to Hiroshima. After the recent raids, the roads there are quite bad.

01:44:53.550 --> 01:44:55.110
Shoes and Geta are not suitable.

01:44:56.170 --> 01:44:57.400
Can I go?

01:44:58.000 --> 01:44:59.370
Wounded can't go.

01:44:59.530 --> 01:45:02.680
My son was also recently transferred to Hiroshima.

01:45:02.820 --> 01:45:05.150
Will you come with me on the truck tomorrow?

01:45:05.370 --> 01:45:10.130
The people of Hiroshima helped us when we were bombed, we also should...

01:45:13.330 --> 01:45:16.910
Look at all those braid. There's no problem with me.

01:45:17.170 --> 01:45:17.840
You can't go!

01:45:18.800 --> 01:45:22.200
Again with this? Let's finish it quickly and go home.

01:45:22.600 --> 01:45:26.240
Our family went to Hiroshima recently.

01:45:26.620 --> 01:45:29.480
They say they dropped a new kind of bomb on Hiroshima.

01:45:29.480 --> 01:45:30.910
It's a...

01:45:31.350 --> 01:45:33.280
Suzu, is your family...

01:45:32.660 --> 01:45:33.620
Mom!

01:45:35.000 --> 01:45:39.020
People were also sent to the army base. But...

01:45:49.060 --> 01:45:51.330
Did you also fly from Hiroshima?

01:46:06.660 --> 01:46:09.170
He just sat here and died.

01:46:09.530 --> 01:46:12.260
Apparently, he came on foot from Hiroshima.

01:46:12.730 --> 01:46:17.220
We never found who he was. Both his face and body were burnt.

01:46:17.220 --> 01:46:19.640
Keep a secret from miss Hojo.

01:46:19.640 --> 01:46:23.280
It's a scary poor thing to look at.

01:46:25.970 --> 01:46:30.310
I collected the eucalyptus leaves.
They help with the mosquitoes.

01:46:31.550 --> 01:46:34.970
Thank you. Hold on, be strong.

01:46:35.280 --> 01:46:35.910
Yes.

01:46:36.150 --> 01:46:40.460
The Urano family from Eba: Jūrō, Kiseno and Sumi

01:46:41.770 --> 01:46:45.480
And the Morita Morita family from Kusatsu: Marino and Tizuko.

01:46:47.240 --> 01:46:51.880
I want to be strong. Kind and strong.

01:46:52.260 --> 01:46:53.930
As the inhabitants of our city.

01:46:54.750 --> 01:46:59.350
Oh, come on! We will not succumb to your threats.

01:46:57.970 --> 01:47:02.390
August 9

01:47:00.680 --> 01:47:02.620
Let me stay here.

01:47:05.510 --> 01:47:11.420
I was so worried and you're a fool. Fool! Fool! Fool!

01:47:12.110 --> 01:47:13.420
I'm sorry.

01:47:14.750 --> 01:47:16.260
I'm sorry.

01:47:16.510 --> 01:47:18.310
I'm really sorry.

01:47:19.310 --> 01:47:20.420
I'm sorry!

01:47:20.530 --> 01:47:22.040
I didn't manage to hit anything.

01:47:22.650 --> 01:47:24.910
I will become the laughingstock of the whole fleet.

01:47:26.280 --> 01:47:30.060
Suzu, why did you collect enemy flyers?

01:47:30.310 --> 01:47:32.350
You're going to be lectured by the kempeitai.

01:47:33.170 --> 01:47:35.440
Even If you give them away, they will just burn them.

01:47:35.820 --> 01:47:39.370
It's good paper, if you stretched it, it's fine for the toilet.

01:47:39.970 --> 01:47:44.110
Indeed. But you will have to not let other people into the toilet.

01:47:44.640 --> 01:47:48.570
We use everything to survive. This is our battle.

01:47:48.570 --> 01:47:49.570
Yeah...

01:47:50.560 --> 01:47:55.530
August 15

01:47:51.150 --> 01:47:52.420
Come in, please.

01:47:52.420 --> 01:47:53.640
Thank you.

01:47:55.550 --> 01:48:02.770
Our first duty is to care for those who have lost their homes and livelihoods.

01:48:03.350 --> 01:48:12.600
For the sake of the great peace for all generations to come, we must endure the unbearable.

01:48:12.640 --> 01:48:19.370
Strengthen the courage of the spirit, work hard to exalt the glory of the imperial state.

01:48:19.480 --> 01:48:24.240
You just listened to the Emperor's message to the people.

01:48:23.370 --> 01:48:24.600
It's all over.

01:48:24.800 --> 01:48:25.920
But it comes out...

01:48:25.920 --> 01:48:28.170
that we lost.

01:48:29.200 --> 01:48:30.170
How's that?

01:48:30.170 --> 01:48:33.550
They dropped these terrible bombs on Hiroshima and Nagasaki.

01:48:33.550 --> 01:48:37.170
And the Soviets entered the war, what can you do...

01:48:38.330 --> 01:48:40.540
How can you say that?

01:48:41.120 --> 01:48:43.770
Shouldn't we fight to the last?

01:48:44.440 --> 01:48:46.550
There are five of us living here!

01:48:46.880 --> 01:48:49.930
My left hand is in place, and so are both my feet!

01:48:58.280 --> 01:48:59.350
Harumi!

01:49:00.840 --> 01:49:02.370
Harumi!

01:49:09.660 --> 01:49:10.990
They are flying away.

01:49:11.400 --> 01:49:16.060
Everything that we thought was right before.

01:49:16.820 --> 01:49:19.680
Everything for which we have endured so much.

01:49:22.360 --> 01:49:25.510
What about rice from behind the sea? And soybeans?

01:49:25.860 --> 01:49:29.150
Our lives depended on them.

01:49:30.460 --> 01:49:33.460
Is it possible to drop on your hands in front of brute force?

01:49:36.710 --> 01:49:41.260
It would be better to die and don't know anything.

01:49:54.260 --> 01:49:58.840
I hid it to eat together when the last day comes.

01:50:00.460 --> 01:50:03.060
Today we will eat pure rice.

01:50:03.550 --> 01:50:09.150
But not all of it. We'll leave some for tomorrow and the next day.

01:50:14.850 --> 01:50:18.910
And after the fifteenth of August came the sixteenth.

01:50:20.170 --> 01:50:21.790
And then the seventeenth.

01:50:23.220 --> 01:50:24.200
And then September.

01:50:25.710 --> 01:50:26.680
And October.

01:50:27.710 --> 01:50:29.350
And November, like last year.

01:50:30.440 --> 01:50:33.370
And the year before that and like ten years ago.

01:50:34.480 --> 01:50:36.750
The same as always.

01:50:48.150 --> 01:50:50.530
It's so white and shiny.

01:50:50.800 --> 01:50:52.530
But we got nothing else.

01:50:52.820 --> 01:50:53.840
It's all right.

01:50:54.310 --> 01:50:55.330
And Shūsaku?

01:50:55.710 --> 01:50:56.280
He's working.

01:50:57.020 --> 01:51:01.150
It's the duty of the Legal Service to maintain order with the troops.

01:51:01.930 --> 01:51:03.400
Let's eat.

01:51:05.970 --> 01:51:08.710
The bombings have stopped so the fish are no longer dying.

01:51:09.080 --> 01:51:10.480
That's correct.

01:51:22.510 --> 01:51:24.150
What are we doing?

01:51:24.310 --> 01:51:26.600
This rice needs a good light.

01:51:37.620 --> 01:51:42.590
October 6

01:51:39.350 --> 01:51:41.130
They finally landed.

01:51:41.800 --> 01:51:43.350
I'm being transferred to Otake.

01:51:44.260 --> 01:51:46.330
Until the fleet is dissolved.

01:51:46.530 --> 01:51:50.530
The Legal Service will
be needed to keep order.

01:51:51.600 --> 01:51:55.310
If I had two hands,

01:51:55.510 --> 01:51:59.800
I would hold on to him and share his unease.

01:52:01.660 --> 01:52:02.880
The streets are empty.

01:52:03.110 --> 01:52:04.400
Everyone's ready.

01:52:04.600 --> 01:52:13.600
Consultation with
victims of the air raids
Kure government agencies

01:52:05.150 --> 01:52:07.640
I'm sorry, but I'm going.

01:52:09.310 --> 01:52:11.020
Get back home quickly.

01:52:12.240 --> 01:52:13.000
So long.

01:52:16.220 --> 01:52:19.840
I'll definitely come back home to you!

01:52:21.080 --> 01:52:21.820
Of course!

01:52:23.070 --> 01:52:26.530
The transmitted board

01:52:23.070 --> 01:52:26.530
Today's rice distribution is postponed.

01:52:23.070 --> 01:52:26.530
Upper Nagano Neighbor Association

01:52:24.370 --> 01:52:27.660
It's been a long time since we last have salt and soy sauce.

01:52:27.170 --> 01:52:32.140
November

01:52:33.080 --> 01:52:34.370
Ah! Sister.

01:52:34.370 --> 01:52:37.200
Oh, Suzu, what's the line for?

01:52:37.550 --> 01:52:39.770
I don't know. What difference does it make?

01:52:39.910 --> 01:52:41.770
Now everything is missing.

01:52:42.680 --> 01:52:43.710
Indeed.

01:52:45.150 --> 01:52:48.400
However, the city has changed a lot.

01:52:48.770 --> 01:52:49.950
Give me!

01:52:50.110 --> 01:52:55.370
I guess Hisao's asking me that now.
And Harumi would have done the same thing.

01:52:55.370 --> 01:52:58.950
Leftovers from the American army.

01:53:01.480 --> 01:53:02.640
It's got piece of paper.

01:53:14.110 --> 01:53:16.110
Yummy!

01:53:18.620 --> 01:53:21.000
Our food is completely tasteless.

01:53:22.570 --> 01:53:27.510
I showed the way to the American soldiers and they gave me some chocolate.

01:53:27.640 --> 01:53:31.110
With that haircut, they took you for a child.

01:53:31.330 --> 01:53:32.040
Hehe.

01:53:37.170 --> 01:53:40.750
Aren't you sorry to exchange good clothes for food?

01:53:41.460 --> 01:53:42.420
Not at all.

01:53:43.480 --> 01:53:49.970
You know, the soldier that sat down and died near the council building, he was probably my son.

01:53:51.000 --> 01:53:53.800
And I didn't even notice him.

01:53:55.600 --> 01:53:58.240
Harumi died in front of your eyes.

01:53:59.530 --> 01:54:02.020
Yes, it was terrible.

01:54:06.040 --> 01:54:06.730
Suzu.

01:54:09.200 --> 01:54:09.800
Suzu.

01:54:10.950 --> 01:54:14.730
Just remember me and smile.

01:54:17.460 --> 01:54:23.680
Remain the most common person in the world, Suzu.

01:54:24.190 --> 01:54:25.360
Harumi.

01:54:25.870 --> 01:54:28.600
Do you see the ship that stands in the harbor, Harumi?

01:54:29.820 --> 01:54:32.550
You know, this is the Aoba.

01:54:34.950 --> 01:54:39.130
Tetsu, as soon as you smile,

01:54:39.640 --> 01:54:45.310
white rabbits appear on the waves and migratory herons in the sky.

01:54:50.080 --> 01:54:52.040
Harumi looks and laughs.

01:54:52.150 --> 01:54:55.770
When I think of Harumi, I smile.

01:54:56.200 --> 01:55:00.130
I'll always be smiling now.

01:55:00.420 --> 01:55:01.600
And rightly so.

01:55:01.770 --> 01:55:04.170
What's the point of crying for pity.

01:55:04.840 --> 01:55:06.600
Only salt to spend.

01:55:08.060 --> 01:55:11.060
How delicious it is with sea salt!

01:55:11.660 --> 01:55:14.880
Auntie, grandmother, Chizuko!

01:55:12.000 --> 01:55:16.880
January

01:55:15.710 --> 01:55:16.460
You're here.

01:55:16.460 --> 01:55:17.530
Suzu!

01:55:19.880 --> 01:55:20.800
Sumi?

01:55:22.170 --> 01:55:23.150
Suzu!

01:55:23.440 --> 01:55:25.280
Did you cut your hair?

01:55:25.510 --> 01:55:28.480
Don't get up, you're sick.

01:55:29.040 --> 01:55:30.970
I'm just a little dizzy.

01:55:31.080 --> 01:55:31.880
Really?

01:55:32.150 --> 01:55:34.640
Forgive me, dear sister.

01:55:34.910 --> 01:55:38.970
On this cold day I will shy away from collecting the nori.

01:55:41.170 --> 01:55:44.370
You deserve an honest rest.

01:55:48.530 --> 01:55:54.400
If I still had my right hand, I would draw the adventures of the devil-brother to cheer you up.

01:55:54.800 --> 01:55:57.860
The adventures? And what were they like?

01:55:58.040 --> 01:56:01.640
When the ship he was on sank.

01:56:02.510 --> 01:56:06.280
He swam to a tiny tropical island.

01:56:06.750 --> 01:56:10.910
He stayed there and took a crocodile as his wife.

01:56:11.240 --> 01:56:13.480
A crocodile, huh?

01:56:14.800 --> 01:56:17.550
He'll never come back to Eba, our brother.

01:56:18.170 --> 01:56:19.550
And Mom too.

01:56:19.770 --> 01:56:20.480
Eh?

01:56:21.000 --> 01:56:26.220
That day she went to the city, to prepare for the festival.

01:56:27.350 --> 01:56:32.130
Dad and I searched for her for many days, but we didn't find her.

01:56:32.750 --> 01:56:36.750
Dad got sick and died in October.

01:56:37.000 --> 01:56:39.660
He was cremated at school with everyone.

01:56:40.060 --> 01:56:43.080
I'm sorry I didn't tell you earlier.

01:56:44.710 --> 01:56:47.170
I'm sorry I didn't come earlier.

01:56:47.770 --> 01:56:49.930
It's nice of you not to have been here so early.

01:56:50.880 --> 01:56:53.840
Suzu, what's wrong with me.

01:56:54.480 --> 01:56:56.770
Will it pass or not?

01:56:56.770 --> 01:56:59.680
It will pass!  It would be strange not to be!

01:57:02.910 --> 01:57:07.680
♪ In the coldest winter

01:57:07.330 --> 01:57:08.200
Sachiko!

01:57:08.830 --> 01:57:17.760
♪ suddenly a warm wind blows.

01:57:09.460 --> 01:57:10.200
Excuse me.

01:57:13.710 --> 01:57:14.710
Kyoko!

01:57:15.150 --> 01:57:16.280
Kyoko, is that you?

01:57:18.510 --> 01:57:22.460
In this city everyone is looking for missing relatives.

01:57:20.930 --> 01:57:31.940
♪ And brings the smell of the sea wave.

01:57:23.040 --> 01:57:27.350
A couple of times I was mistaken for someone else.

01:57:28.950 --> 01:57:29.770
Suzu.

01:57:32.880 --> 01:57:39.390
REVIVAL

01:57:33.200 --> 01:57:34.570
You're alive.

01:57:35.370 --> 01:57:39.420
The fleet has been officially dissolved since November, and I am unemployed.

01:57:40.620 --> 01:57:46.800
Suzu, do you remember how we first met on this bridge?

01:57:40.680 --> 01:57:50.670
♪ Some shards on the way sparkle and laugh.

01:57:48.260 --> 01:57:50.260
There's no going back to that time.

01:57:50.890 --> 01:58:02.360
♪ You are pushed by the sunny hands.

01:57:50.910 --> 01:57:54.400
Us and the city, everything became different.

01:57:54.550 --> 01:57:56.750
But I can always recognize you.

01:57:57.350 --> 01:58:00.000
That mole on your cheek is not mistaken.

01:58:01.240 --> 01:58:03.170
Thank you, Shūsaku.

01:58:03.730 --> 01:58:07.330
You've found me in this corner of the world.

01:58:07.860 --> 01:58:12.350
Don't go away anymore, be with me forever.

01:58:16.230 --> 01:58:21.780
♪ You are hugged by a sunset from nori.

01:58:38.280 --> 01:58:44.260
♪ No longer hear the sparrows talking.

01:58:49.140 --> 01:58:54.520
♪ Do not swim in the dandelion fluff.

01:58:55.070 --> 01:59:01.770
♪ One cannot find the gleam among the clouds.

01:59:01.770 --> 01:59:12.080
♪ It's hard to know what your neighbors are dreaming of.

01:59:13.790 --> 01:59:22.800
♪ It does not go all past.

01:59:24.860 --> 01:59:25.710
No no no.

01:59:26.200 --> 01:59:29.860
I'm so lucky to get a job in Hiroshima anyway.

01:59:27.260 --> 01:59:38.240
♪ One after another, these sparkling days become memories.

01:59:30.060 --> 01:59:30.680
Yes.

01:59:34.060 --> 01:59:37.970
But driving here is far away. I'd like to...

01:59:42.900 --> 01:59:51.660
♪ And you cannot do anything about it.

01:59:42.950 --> 01:59:46.040
Thank you. You can eat it yourself.

01:59:46.840 --> 01:59:49.860
Leave the house and settle here?

01:59:50.840 --> 01:59:52.950
You have to take care of Sumi and Mom.

01:59:53.600 --> 01:59:57.310
No, I'd rather come here more often.

01:59:55.250 --> 02:00:04.130
♪ You are just one of the pieces of this vast world.

01:59:57.860 --> 02:00:03.130
I'm worried about Hiroshima, but I chose Kure as my home.

02:00:05.420 --> 02:00:16.920
♪ You're just one of the pieces,

02:00:15.790 --> 02:00:18.800
TICKETS

02:00:22.220 --> 02:00:29.320
♪ which someone for some reason collects.

02:00:23.750 --> 02:00:27.460
Kure! Kure!

02:00:27.260 --> 02:00:28.060
Kure?

02:00:28.680 --> 02:00:30.970
Yes, this is Kure.

02:00:31.560 --> 02:00:41.290
♪ So, your cherished place always waits for you.

02:00:31.680 --> 02:00:35.930
Nine mountain peaks protect our city.

02:00:37.000 --> 02:00:38.600
On the right, Yasumi-yama.

02:00:39.600 --> 02:00:41.640
On the left, Hachimaki-yama

02:00:43.000 --> 02:00:46.570
And this one, right in the center, Haigamine.

02:00:48.570 --> 02:00:53.180
♪ Love is everywhere.

02:00:49.970 --> 02:00:52.730
At the foot of it is our house.

02:00:53.600 --> 02:00:59.060
♪ Love is everywhere.

02:00:59.600 --> 02:01:04.980
♪ In this changing world

02:01:01.930 --> 02:01:02.910
Who's this kid?

02:01:05.350 --> 02:01:07.510
Look how dirty she is!

02:01:05.610 --> 02:01:21.080
♪ then there, here, there are pieces of love.

02:01:08.280 --> 02:01:11.820
Go and heat up the bathwater.
Who's going to boil the clothes?

02:01:12.400 --> 02:01:14.040
While she's in the tub.

02:01:14.460 --> 02:01:17.350
Looks like she didn't wash for a long time.

02:01:17.350 --> 02:01:18.730
Let's go to the bath.

02:01:20.330 --> 02:01:23.970
Here's some of Harumi's old clothes. It's small enough I guess...

02:01:24.110 --> 02:01:26.730
♪ Look.

02:01:26.750 --> 02:01:37.550
♪ They become one more particle of you.

02:01:58.460 --> 02:02:02.510
The seed that the bird carried

02:02:03.210 --> 02:02:07.450
I'm breathing quietly.

02:02:08.200 --> 02:02:12.410
What kind of scenery will spreads?

02:02:12.410 --> 02:02:18.670
I envision it in the soil.

02:02:26.540 --> 02:02:30.680
Let's take a peek.

02:02:31.310 --> 02:02:35.630
I'm just a little bit scared

02:02:36.240 --> 02:02:40.480
I want to see the world that fills my eyes

02:02:40.480 --> 02:02:47.160
This feeling is not shaken.

02:02:50.300 --> 02:02:58.490
When the color of the wind changes

02:03:00.270 --> 02:03:09.840
When rainy thorns are gone

02:03:29.050 --> 02:03:33.280
To you, this world

02:03:33.710 --> 02:03:38.270
What does it look like?

02:03:38.490 --> 02:03:42.840
Here I am taking roots

02:03:42.870 --> 02:03:48.000
With a sigh in the middle of a dream

02:03:48.000 --> 02:04:03.740
The fluff fills the sky far away

02:04:03.740 --> 02:04:07.600
Skip it.

02:04:30.330 --> 02:04:35.120
A wish that cannot be fulfilled

02:04:35.120 --> 02:04:39.600
A feelings that never reach

02:04:39.600 --> 02:04:44.200
Become a deep deep color

02:04:44.220 --> 02:04:50.890
To dye me gently

02:04:53.130 --> 02:04:56.510
Over that roof.

02:04:57.880 --> 02:05:01.340
To the next town

02:05:02.920 --> 02:05:11.020
To the garden of someone I don't know

02:05:13.070 --> 02:05:16.190
Some of them are stepped on

02:05:17.740 --> 02:05:21.680
Some of them are on the ship.

02:05:22.520 --> 02:05:31.180
If you can reach your shoulder

02:05:49.880 --> 02:05:53.850
A small fire is burning.

02:05:54.700 --> 02:05:58.540
There's no sound in the soil

02:05:59.550 --> 02:06:03.860
When the time comes for a free tomorrow

02:06:03.860 --> 02:06:11.480
I'm sure I'll see you.

